ity-2021-8%5C%22%3EChinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping's%20push%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bcommon%20prosperity%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20long%20had%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6289559%2Fchina-inequality-wealth-flaunting-common-prosperity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euneasy%20relationship%20with%20the%20pursuit%20of%20luxury%20goods%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20affluent%20lifestyle.%20The%20government%20has%20spent%20over%20a%20decade%20discouraging%20ostentatious%20displays%20of%20affluence.%20Back%20in%202011%2C%20the%20authorities%20started%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworldnews%2Fasia%2Fchina%2F8398097%2FChina-bans-luxury-advertising-in-Beijing.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanning%20billboards%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20terms%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bluxury%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20class%26quot%3B%20in%20Beijing.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20China%20banned%20civil%20servants%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-china-luxury%2Fchinas-corruption-crackdown-takes-shine-off-luxury-boom-idUSBRE88M0F020120923%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccepting%20expensive%20gifts%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB10001424052702303740704577520462755862808%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20public%20funds%20to%20host%20extravagant%20dinners%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20extended%20to%20the%20government's%20oversight%20over%20social%20media.%20In%202021%2C%20China's%20version%20of%20TikTok%2C%20Douyin%2C%20said%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjingdaily.com%2Fdouyin-bans-wealth-bragging-xuanfu-luxury%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeleted%20thousands%20of%20accounts%20and%20videos%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20excessive%20displays%20of%20