20sambar%20and%20kesari.%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20I%20would%20be%20famished%20by%2011%20am%20and%20eagerly%20wait%20for%20the%20bell%20to%20ring%20to%20have%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20provided%20at%20the%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20child%20grinned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMore%20than%2070%25%20of%20the%20students%20do%20not%20have%20breakfast%20at%20home.%20We%20were%20happy%20that%20the%20students%20enjoyed%20the%20breakfast.%20No%20one%20wasted%20the%20food.%20The%20dull%2C%20inactive%20faces%20of%20the%20children%20lit%20up%20with%20happiness%2C%E2%80%9D%20V.%20Umaparvathy%20at%20the%20Saidapet%20school%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1.jpeg%20750w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1-300x150.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669962%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESchoolchildren%20being%20served%20breakfast.%20Photo%3A%20Laasya%20Shekhar%2FSouth%20First%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EImproved%20attendance%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20positive%20impact%20of%20this%20programme%20extends%20far%20beyond%20filling%20empty%20stomachs.%20A%20recent%20study%20conducted%20by%20the%20State%20Planning%20Commission%20found%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20attendance%20among%20government%20schools%20implementing%20the%20breakfast%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20out%20of%20the%201%2C543%20schools%20where%20children%20have%20been%20receiving%20breakfast%20since%2015%20September%2C%202022%2C%201%2C319%20schools%20witnessed%20a%20remarkable%20rise%20in%20attendance%20during%20January%20and%20February%2C%20compared%20to%20June-July%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20base%20attendance%20data%20of%20the%20initial%201%2C543%20beneficiary%20schools%20was%20compared%20against%20that%20of%20neighbouring%20schools%20within%201-2%20km%20by%20considering%20the%20geographical%20coordinates%20of%20the%20schools%2C%20reported%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ffree-breakfast-scheme-has-improved-attendance-in-schools-tamil-nadu-govt-study-1200572.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20considered%20only%20schools%20with%20enrolment%20of%2025%20and%20above%20and%20schools%20with%20consistent%20attendance%20reporting%20above%2075%25.%20This%20left%20the%20study%20with%2072%20beneficiary%20schools%20each%20mapped%20with%20at%20least%20two%20to%2015%20neighbouring%20schools%2C%20which%20took%20the%20total%20to%20414.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQuick%20rewind%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20many%20pioneering%20schemes%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20providing%20food%20to%20the%20school%20children%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20an%20initiative%20that%20improved%20the%20attendance%20and%20reduced%20malnutrition%20among%20socially%20struggling%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1920%3A%20The%20then%20Mayor%20of%20Chennai%20Corporation%2C%20Sir%20PT%20Thiyagarayar%2C%20passed%20a%20resolution%20to%20implement%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20in%20Corporation%20School%20at%20Thousand%20Lights%2C%20Chennai.%20The%20scheme%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20school%E2%80%99s%20student%20strength.%20The%20scheme%20was%20expanded%20to%20a%20few%20more%20schools%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1947%3A%20Due%20to%20financial%20constraints%2C%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20was%20abandoned%2C%20except%20in%20Harijan%20Welfare%20Department-run%20schools.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1957%3A%20Chief%20minister%20K%20Kamaraj%20resumed%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20for%20primary%20school%20students.%20%E2%82%B910%20lakh%20was%20allotted%20for%20implementing%20this%20scheme%2C%20with%20a%20clause%20that%20it%20should%20not%20exceeding%20%E2%82%B918%20per%20child%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1982%3A%20Chief%20minister%20MG%20Ramachandran%20introduced%20the%20Nutritious%20Meal%20Programme.%20Children%20in%20pre-school%20and%20primary%20schools%20were%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1989%3A%C2%A0%20Chief%20minister%20M%20Karunanidhi%20included%20an%20egg%20every%20two%20weeks%20to%20the%20menu%20of%20the%20nutritious%20meal%20scheme.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1998-2008%3A%20The%20egg%20count%20gradually%20increased%20from%20one%20per%20week%20to%20three%20per%20week.%20The%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20provided%20bananas%20for%20the%20children%20who%20would%20not%20eat%20eggs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E2010%3A%20Egg%20count%20goes%20to%20five%20every%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Ftamilnadu%2Ftn-extends-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools-brings-cheer-to-17-lakh-primary-students%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20South%20First.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693036826000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121001%2FBreakfast-scheme-in-Chennai-2-750x500-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Ftamil-nadu-extends-acclaimed-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Chief%20Minister's%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20provides%20breakfast%20to%20primary%20school%20children%2C%20addressing%20hunger%20and%20improving%20attendance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Ftamil-nadu-extends-acclaimed-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BMisinformation%20Biggest%20Risk%20For%20A%20Democratic%20Country%26quot%3B%3A%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20to%20NDTV%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EInternet%20shutdown%20is%20always%20the%20last%20resort%20and%20it%20is%20also%20not%20unique%20to%20India%2C%20Union%20Minister%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20said%20at%20the%20NDTV%20G20%20Conclave%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20the%20Union%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Electronics%20and%20Technology%2C%20said%20the%20spread%20of%20misinformation%20is%20the%20biggest%20risk%20for%20any%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20snapped%20internet%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20after%20special%20status%20was%20scrapped.%20There%20is%20also%20partial%20internet%20blackout%20in%20ethnic%20violence-hit%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20coming%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20can%20take%20misinformation%20to%20the%20next%20level%20with%20deep%20fakes%20and%20other%20methods%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar%20said%20at%20the%20G20%20Conclave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20internet%20shutdowns%20are%20meant%20to%20stop%20the%20spread%20of%20misinformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20the%20example%20of%20the%20hugely%20successful%20United%20Payments%20Interface