0height%3D%5C%22327%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Trading%20Economics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20a%20rise%20in%20loanable%20funds%20will%20be%20a%20consequence%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20monetary%20policy%20anchored%20by%20the%20RBI%20and%20the%20fiscal%20policy%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%20So%20far%2C%20amidst%20rising%20inflation%2C%20higher%20interest%20rates%20(that%20affect%20borrowing-lending%20patterns)%20will%20negatively%20affect%20the%20ability%20of%20banks%20to%20provide%20cheaper%20credit%20to%20the%20private%20sector%20(assuming%20there%20is%20demand%20for%20such%20credit).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121736%2Fimage5.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22714%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121736%2Fimage5.png%20714w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121736%2Fimage5-300x141.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669967%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22335%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Trading%20Economics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20we%20look%20at%20the%20numbers%20more%20closely%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20core%20inflation%20rate%20has%20remained%20higher%20than%20the%20bank%20loan%20growth%20from%20late%202019%20onwards%20till%20mid-2022%2C%20and%20since%20then%2C%20loan%20growth%20has%20jumped%20higher%20than%20the%20inflation%20rate.%20Over%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%20though%2C%20a%20higher%20inflation%20rate%20is%20threatening%20the%20banks%E2%80%99%20abilities%20to%20continue%20providing%20more%20credit%20under%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20status%20quo%20(in%20interest%20rate).%20On%20food%20inflation%2C%20price%20patterns%20have%20remained%20extremely%20volatile%20(reflected%20by%20a%20higher%20variance%20from%20the%20mean)%20and%20made%20the%20basic%20household%20consumption%20basket%20more%20expensive%20for%20the%20average%20income-earning%20citizen.%20This%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20recent%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121742%2Fimage6.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22714%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121742%2Fimage6.png%20714w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121742%2Fimage6-300x141.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669968%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22335%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Trading%20Economics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20let%20us%20break%20down%20the%20core%20inflation%20trends.%20The%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20(CPI)%20has%20continuously%20gone%20up%20since%202014%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%20amidst%20stagnating%20and%20falling%20incomes%20for%20the%20middle%20and%20lower-income%2Fconsumption%20classes%20(see%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fright-wing-populism-amid-shifting-economic-paradigm-can-political-left-thrive%23read-more%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20While%20the%20rural%20economy%20tatters%20and%20drags%20itself%20in%20almost%20a%20recession-style%20slowdown%2C%20price%20rise%20has%20made%20the%20situation%20for%20low-income%20earners%20worse.%20It%20is%20also%20severely%20hurting%20the%20ability%20of%20India%E2%8