t%20the%20world%20might%20be%20seeing%20the%20economic%20geography%20shifting%20toward%20Eastern%20nations%2C%20McKinsey%20said%20in%20its%20Driving%20Sustainable%20and%20Inclusive%20Growth%20in%20G20%20Economies%20report%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20world%20remains%20deeply%20interdependent%2C%20and%20indeed%20perhaps%20more%20so%20than%20previously%2C%20as%20digital%20and%20data%20flows%20fuel%20exchanges%20of%20communication%20and%20knowledge%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinsey%20said%20in%20its%20report.%20%26quot%3BYet%20the%20global%20economic%20picture%20suggests%20that%20the%20world%20may%20be%20at%20the%20cusp%20of%20a%20new%20era.%20Economic%20geography%20has%20shifted%20eastward...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20economic%20centres%20are%20likely%20to%20shift%20in%20the%20future%2C%20G20%20economies%20currently%20have%20wide%20and%20varying%20trends%20on%20sustainability%20and%20inclusion.%C2%A0%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22NDTV%20G20%20Conclave%20-%20watch%20live%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspecial.ndtv.com%2Fdecoding-g20-ndtv-conclave-121%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22g20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fdecoding20-1200x738.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20debt%20is%20now%20at%20its%20highest%20levels%20since%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II%2C%20with%20the%20debt-to-gross%20domestic%20product%20ratio%20now%20standing%20at%20more%20than%20300%25%20for%20G20%20countries.%20Inequality%20within%20countries-as%20measured%20by%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20richest%2010%25%20and%20the%20bottom%2050%25-has%20also%20risen%20to%20its%20highest%20level%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20India%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20core%20growth%20engines%20for%20the%20G20%2C%20but%20other%20nations%20score%20better%20on%20inclusion%20and%20sustainability.%20European%20countries%2C%20Japan%20and%20Korea%20are%20well%20advanced%20on%20a%20range%20of%20indicators%20from%20life%20expectancy%20to%20share%20of%20population%20with%20bank%20accounts.%20On%20sustainability%2C%20while%20emerging%20economies%20have%20the%20lowest%20per%20capita%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20countries%20in%20Europe%20have%20the%20lowest%20ratio%20of%20CO2%20emissions%20to%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22ev677bo8%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fev677bo8_indiachina_625x300_26_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20Empowerment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20McKinsey%20report%20talks%20about%20bringing%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20world's%20population%20above%20the%20line%20of%20economic%20empowerment%20to%20score%20better%20on%20metrics%20such%20as%20growth%2C%20inclusion%20and%20sustainability.%20The%20line%20of%20economic%20empowerment%20is%2C%20however%2C%20different%20from%20the%20World%20Bank's%20extreme%20poverty%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20concept%20of%20economic%20empowerment%20described%20in%20this%20research%20involves%20ensuring%20that%20everyone%20has%20the%20means%20to%20access%20the%20full%20range%20of%20basics%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinsey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Bank%20estimates%20the%20extreme%20poverty%20line%20to%20be%20at%20%242.15%20per%20person%20per%20day.%20However%2C%20McKinsey%20quotes%20other%20studies%20which%20state%20that%20in%20emerging%20economies%20on%20purchasing%20power%20parity%20terms%2C%20at%20%2412%20per%20person%20per%20day%20people%20can%20meet%20their%20basic%20needs%20and%20start%20to%20achieve%20discretionary%20spending%20powers.%20This%20is%20also%20the%20point%20where%20the%20risk%20of%20falling%20back%20into%20poverty%20is%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20advanced%20economies%2C%20adjusting%20for%20their%20higher%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20the%20line%20of%20economic%20empowerment%20is%20%2447%20per%20person%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20an%20overall%20basis%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20population%20in%20G20%20economies%2C%20or%202.6%20billion%20people%2C%20live%20under%20the%20line%20of%20economic%20empowerment%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20This%20includes%20100%20million%20people%20living%20in%20extreme%20poverty%2C%202.2%20billion%20people%20living%20under%20the%20line%20of%20economic%20empowerment%20in%20emerging%20economies%20and%20about%20300%20million%20people%20in%20advanced%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22k1312o38%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fk1312o38_economy_625x300_26_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20global%20scale%2C%20the%20number%20of%20such%20people%20is%20at%204.7%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20McKinsey%2C%20more%20than%20three-fourths%20of%20the%20population%20in%20India%20and%20South%20Africa%20live%20below%20this%20line.%20As%20of%202020%2C%2077%25%20of%20India's%20population%20or%201.07%20billion%20people%20and%2075%25%20of%20South%20Africa's%20population%20or%204.4%20million%20people%20lived%20under%20the%20line%20of%20economic%20empowerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20of%20China%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Brazil%20and%20Indonesia%2C%20this%20number%20is%20at%20over%2050%25.%20In%20more%20advanced%20economies%20in%20Europe%20and%20North%20America%2C%20about%2020-30%25%20live%20below%20the%20empowerment%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20analysis%20suggests%20that%20closing%20this%20empowerment%20gap%20in%20G20%20economies%20would%20require%20a%20cumulative%20increase%20in%20spending%20on%20essentials%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20%2421%20trillion%20over%20the%20decade%20to%202030%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinsey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22v0k8avh8%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fv0k8avh8_g20_625x300_26_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20of%20India%2C%20the%20total%20additional%20spending%20required%20between%202021%20and%202030%20is%20at%20%245.3%20trillion%20to%20bridge%20this%20gap.%20This%20accounts%20for%2013%25%20of%20the%20GDP%20during%20this%20decade.%20For%20China%2C%20the%20spends%20required%20are%20at%20%244.8%20trillion%20over%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETowards%20Sustainability%20And%20Inclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20increased%20spending%20is%20one%20aspect%20of%20bridging%20the%20gap%20in%20sustainability%20and%20inclusion%2C%20there%20are%20other%20efforts%20essential%20from%20various%20countries%20to%20meet%20this%20goal%2C%20McKinsey%20said.%20To%20this%20effect%2C%20it%20has%20listed%20various%20public%20and%20private%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20list%20is%20not%20exhaustive%20and%20should%20not%20be%20interpreted%20as%20policy%20recommendations.%20Each%20takes%20place%20in%20a%20particular%20economic%20and%20social%20context%20in%20a%20specific%20country%2C%20and%20the%20learnings%20are%20by%20definition%20not%20universally%20applicable%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinsey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20lists%20various%20programmes%2C%20India%20scores%20as%20an%20exemplar%20in%20eight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22b7ft9s8%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fb7ft9s8_india_625x300_26_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinancial%20And%20Digital%20Inclusion%3A%20According%20to%20McKinsey%2C%20India's%20initiatives%20through%20Jan%20Dhan%20accounts%2C%20Aadhaar%20and%20mobile-popularly%20known%20as%20the%20JAM%20trinity-have%20improved%20financial%20inclusion%20and%20increased%20transparency%20in%20delivery%20of%20government%20subsidies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAffordable%20Housing%3A%20Targeted%20government%20programmes%20for%20lower%20and%20middle-income%20group%20housing%20have%20pushed%20affordability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaccination%3A%20India's%20efforts%20through%20the%20CoWin%20portal%20helped%20build%20a%20holistic%20vaccination%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealthcare%3A%20Apollo%20Hospitals'%20omnichannel%20end-to-end%20healthcare%20system%20boosts%20quality%2C%20affordability%20and%20accessibility%20of%20healthcare%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENutritional%20Crops%3A%20India's%20latest%20initiatives%20to%20increase%20awareness%20and%20production%20of%20millets%20domestically%20and%20globally%20will%20improve%20production%20of%20high%20nutrition%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERenewables%20Push%3A%20India's%20expansion%20of%20its%20solar%20footprint%20through%20the%20government%20and%20achieving%20over%2060%20GW%20solar%20capacity%20in%2012%20years%2C%20from%2010%20MW%2C%20were%20identified%20as%20an%20exemplar%20for%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectric%20Vehicles%3A%20Ola%20Electric's%20rapid%20proliferation%20as%20an%20electric%20two-wheeler%20provider%20added%20to%20India's%20sustainable%20mobility%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECleanliness%3A%20The%20waste%20management%20system%20transformation%20by%20Indore%20Municipal%20Corporation%20was%20an%20exemplar%20for%20circularity%20initiatives%20by%20cities%20around%20G20%20economies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693033320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fnf54vf2_india_625x300_26_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-to-have-one-of-the-largest-working-age-populations-by-2030-mckinsey-4331168%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%2C%20China%20and%20Indonesia%20will%20be%20three%20of%20the%20five%20economies%20with%20the%20world's%20largest%20working-age%20populations%20among%20G20%20countries%20by%202030.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-ne