0Union.%20But%20why%20would%20he%2C%20in%20the%20first%20instance%2C%20choose%20to%20go%20further%20away%2C%20to%20Soviet%20Russia%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fnetaji-subhas-chandra-bose-gumnami-baba%5C%22%3EThe%20Netaji%20Mystery%3A%20Marking%20the%20End%20of%20Another%20%E2%80%98Baba%E2%80%99%20Story%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetaji%20was%20in%20a%20continuous%20cordial%20relationship%20with%20both%20Germany%20and%20Italy%20even%20after%20knowing%20about%20extermination%20camps%20and%20gas%20chambers%20in%20Europe%2C%20about%20the%20genocide%20of%20Ukrainians%2C%20Belorussians%2C%20Jews%2C%20and%20Russians.%20So%2C%20could%20Netaji%20expect%20a%20warm%20welcome%20awaiting%20him%20in%20the%20USSR%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetaji%E2%80%99s%20nephew%20Professor%20Dwarka%20Nath%20Bose%2C%20who%20had%20visited%20the%20Archives%20in%20Russia%20along%20with%20the%20Mukherjee%20Commission%20of%20Inquiry%2C%20highlighted%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20aversion%20to%20Bose.%20He%20narrates%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CSubhas%E2%80%A6.%20was%20eager%20to%20visit%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20as%20he%20was%20an%20admirer%20of%20Soviet%20planning.%20However%2C%20he%20was%20never%20granted%20a%20visa%20for%20this%20purpose%E2%80%A6.%20Jawaharlal%20had%20gone%20to%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20earlier%20with%20his%20father%20and%20so%20had%20Tagore.%20So%2C%20why%20this%20aversion%20to%20Bose%3F%20It%20may%20be%20traced%20to%20his%20speech%20as%20President%20of%20the%20Indian%20Trade%20Union%20Congress%20in%201928%20when%20he%20said%20among%20other%20things%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20has%20done%20great%20damage%20to%20the%20Trade%20Union%20movement.%20They%20take%20their%20instructions%20from%20Russia%2C%20etc.%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6.%20Even%20when%20he%20obtained%20a%20Soviet%20visa%20from%20Afghanistan%20in%201941%20after%20his%20escape%20from%20India%20and%20was%20eager