D%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Fonscreen-bromances-we-can-never-get-enough-of%2Fphotostory%2F103064716.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103064716.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EOnscreen%20Bromances%20We%20Can%20Never%20Get%20Enough%20Of%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Fonscreen-bromances-we-can-never-get-enough-of%2Fphotostory%2F103064716.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Ashoka%20University%20Can%20Learn%20From%20Gandhi%2C%20Tagore%20and%20Nehru's%20Thoughts%20on%20Academic%20Freedom%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14005619%2Fcollage.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20sinister%20development%20in%20Ashoka%20University%20%E2%80%93%20personnel%20from%20the%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20(IB)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fintelligence-bureau-at-ashoka-university-wants-to-probe-democratic-backsliding-paper%5C%22%3Eentering%20the%20campus%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20quiz%20associate%20professor%20Sabyasachi%20Das%20on%20his%20research%20paper%20%E2%80%98Democratic%20Backsliding%20in%20India%20in%20the%20World%E2%80%99s%20Largest%20Democracy%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20constitutes%20an%20example%20of%20intimidation%20and%20flagrant%20violation%20of%20university%20autonomy.%20The%20paper%20argued%20that%20there%20may%20have%20been%20manipulation%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%20in%202019%2C%20benefitting%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConfronted%20with%20sharp%20attacks%20from%20BJP%20leaders%20and%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20distance%20itself%20from%20the%20paper%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fauthor-of-paper-on-possible-manipulation-in-2019-polls-quits-ashoka-university%5C%22%3EDas%20resigned%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Faculty%20members%20and%20students%20were%20outraged%20by%20Ashoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20stand%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Cvalues%20research%20that%20is%20critically%20peer-reviewed%20and%20published%20in%20reputed%20journals%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20the%20best%20of%20our%20knowledge%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20university%20had%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20paper%20in%20question%20has%20not%20yet%20completed%20a%20critical%20review%20process%20and%20has%20not%20been%20published%20in%20an%20academic%20journal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20appalling%20example%20of%20the%20suppression%20of%20academic%20freedom%20and%20creativity%20in%20a%20higher%20educational%20institution.%20Such%20freedom%20is%20indispensable%20for%20any%20university%20to%20pursue%20academic%20activities%20celebrating%20originality%20and%20anchored%20in%20rigorous%20research.%20It%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20powers%20that%20be%20at%20in%20the%20Union%20government%20are%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20exercising%20influence%20over%20the%20authorities%20at%20Ashoka%20University%20to%20sternly%20convey%20the%20message%20that%20study%2C%20research%20and%20publication%20of%20articles%20critical%20of%20the%20regime%20are%20unacceptable%20and%20would%20be%20visited%20with%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGandhi%20on%20the%20British%20regime%E2%80%99s%20control%20over%20universities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20India%20is%20witnessing%20in%20the%20form%20of%20an%20all-out%20assault%20on%20the%20autonomy%20of%20Ashoka%20University%20and%20its%20regrettable%20capitulation%20to%20such%20menacing%20interferences%20reminds%20one%20of%20British%20rule%2C%20when%20universities%20of%20pre-independent%20India%20were%20being%20controlled%20by%20the%20colonial%20government%20directly%20or%20indirectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20best%20evidenced%20by%20M.K.%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20address%20at%20a%20students%E2%80%99%20meeting%20in%20Benaras%20on%20November%2026%2C%201920%2C%20during%20the%20non-cooperation%20movement.%20In%20his%20speech%2C%20he%20appealed%20to%20the%20students%20to%20boycott%20even%20Benaras%20University%20if%20they%20felt%20that%20the%20Lieutenant-Governor%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20his%20assertion%20that%20the%20government%20exercised%20no%20control%20over%20the%20university%2C%20actually%20influenced%20it%20indirectly.%20In%20saying%20so%2C%20Gandhi%20was%20clearly%20conveying%20to%20the%20students%20that%20the%20British%20government%20was%20interfering%20in%20the%20internal%20affairs%20of%20the%20university%20in%20some%20form%20or%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20again%20in%20the%20same%20address%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20tell%20you%2C%20so%20long%20as%20the%20influence%20of%20this%20Empire%20reaches%20the%20university%20directly%20or%20indirectly%2C%20you%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20leave%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Gandhi%20was%20driving%20home%20the%20point%20that%20the%20probability%20of%20the%20British%20government%20dictating%20that%20a%20university%20act%20in%20a%20particular%20manner%20was%20very%20high%20and%20almost%20certain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20hundred%20and%20three%20years%20later%2C%20when%20India%20is%20celebrating%20the%2076th%20anniversary%20of%20its%20independence%2C%20the%20country%20is%20witnessing%20the%20sordid%20spectacle%20of%20IB%20officials%20being%20ordered%20to%20interrogate%20an%20academic%20and%20even%20other%20faculty%20members%2C%20to%20ascertain%20if%20he%20himself%20authored%20the%20aforementioned%20research%20paper%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fib-team-at-ashoka-university-asked-if-paper-on-democratic-backsliding-was-a-solo-effort-reports%5C%22%3Eothers%20collaborated%20with%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20give%20shape%20to%20it.%20So%20are%20we%20confronting%20a%20replay%20of%20the%20British%20colonial%20era%20in%202023%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20precious%20%C2%A0autonomy%20so%20critical%20to%20the%20functioning%20of%20universities%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Ashoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20Descent%20into%20Academic%20(un)Freedom%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fashoka-universitys-descent-into-academic-unfreedom%5C%22%3EAshoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20Descent%20into%20Academic%20(un)Freedom%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETagore%20on%20universities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20it%20is%20worthwhile%20to%20recall%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20words.%20In%201925%2C%20in%20a%20highly%20critical%20article%20on%20the%20functioning%20of%20universities%20during%20British%20rule%2C%20he%20observed%20that%20those%20academic%20bodies%20were%20like%20%E2%80%9Chard-boiled%20eggs%20from%20which%20you%20cannot%20expect%20chickens%20to%20come%20out%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%20100%20years%20later%2C%20we%20are%20witnessing%20with%20consternation%20the%20clampdown%20on%20universities%20%E2%80%93%20which%20because%20of%20the%20severe%20curtailment%20of%20academic%20freedom%20are%20becoming%20like%20%E2%80%9Chard-boiled%20eggs%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20track%20record%20of%20professor%20Pratab%20Bhanu%20Mehta%20exiting%20Ashoka%20University%20indicated%20the%20growing%20crisis%20affecting%20the%20autonomy%20of%20that%20university.%20Students%20and%20teachers%20who%20disapproved%20of%20Das%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20and%20demanded%20his%20restoration%20as%20a%20teacher%20drew%20parallels%20with%20Mehta%2C%20who%20had%20to%20quit%20initially%20as%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20vice-chancellor%20and%20later%20as%20its%20professor%20because%20of%20his%20numerous%20newspaper%20criticising%20the%20politics%20and%20policies%20of%20the%20BJP%20regime.%20Professor%20Arvind%20Subramanian%20too%20resigned%20from%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Farvind-subramanian-ashoka-university-academic-freedom-pratap-bhanu-mehta%5C%22%3Estating%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6despite%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20private%20backing%2C%20it%20was%20still%20unable%20to%20provide%20a%20space%20for%20academic%20expression%20and%20freedom.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20employment%20of%20IB%20personnel%20for%20questioning%20Das%20is%20even%20incompatible%20with%20the%20declaratory%20objectives%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20New%20Education%20Policy%20(NEP)%202020%2C%20tom-tommed%20by%20the%20present%20regime%20at%20the%20Centre%20as%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6the%20first%20education%20policy%20of%20the%2021st%20century%E2%80%9D.%20It%20proclaims%20that%20apart%20from%20enhancing%20cognitive%20capacities%2C%20it%20would%20promote%20critical%20thinking.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20is%20quite%20imperative%20to%20ask%20how%20IB%20inquiries%20on%20a%20research%20paper%20serve%20the%20objectives%20set%20out%20in%20the%20NEP%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENehru%20on%20universities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20formative%20stage%20of%20our%20independence%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20brilliantly%20outlined%20the%20role%20of%20a%20university%20by%20saying%2C%20it%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6stands%20for%20humanism%2C%20for%20tolerance%2C%20for%20reason%2C%20for%20progress%2C%20for%20the%20adventure%20of%20ideas%20and%20for%20the%20search%20for%20truth%E2%80%9D.%20That%20lofty%20vision%20of%20a%20university%20was%20articulated%20by%20him%20in%201947%20while%20speaking%20at%20Allahabad%20University%2C%20when%20the%20country%20faced%20a%20communal%20conflagration%20following%20Partition.%20He%20then%20warned%20that%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6if%20the%20temple%20of%20learning%20becomes%20a%20home%20of%20narrow%20bigotry%20and%20petty%20objectives%2C%20how%20then%20will%20the%20nation%20prosper%20or%20a%20people%20grow%20in%20stature%3F%20%E2%80%A6We%20are%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cgoing%20to%20reach%20our%20goal%20through%20crookedness%20or%20flirting%20with%20evil%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20it%20may%20lead%20to%20good.%E2%80%9D%20He%20then%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20right%20end%20can%20never%20be%20fully%20achieved%20through%20wrong%20means.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Safeguarding%20Academic%20Freedom%20Is%20the%20Bedrock%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitutional%20Morality%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsafeguarding-academic-freedom-is-the-bedrock-of-indias-constitutional-morality%5C%22%3ESafeguarding%20Academic%20Freedom%20Is%20the%20Bedrock%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitutional%20Morality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%E2%80%99s%20espousal%20in%201947%20for%20eschewing%20%E2%80%9Cnarrow%20bigotry%20and%20petty%20objectives%E2%80%9D%20so%20that%20universities%20would%20render%20services%20to%20the%20country%20is%20of%20abiding%20significance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20week%20before%20independence%2C%20on%20August%207%2C%201947%2C%20Gandhi%20wrote%20that%20universities%20%E2%80%9Cmust%20stimulate%20the%20faculty%20of%20thinking%E2%80%9D%20and%20students%20%E2%80%9Chave%20to%20create%20public%20opinion%20by%20offering%20constructive%20and%20enlightened%20criticism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authorities%20of%20Ashoka%20University%20must%20pay%20heed%20to%20these%20sane%20voices%20to%20defend%20academic%20freedom%20so%20essential%20to%20uphold%20intellectual%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%20to%20President%20of%20India%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693017045000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14005619%2Fcollage.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fwhat-ashoka-university-