014%2C%20Modi%20oversaw%20an%20administration%20that%20sparked%20rapid%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20model%20is%20based%20on%20the%20old%20Gujarati%20tradition%20of%20collaboration%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20corporate%20sector%2C%20the%20maintenance%20of%20low%20wages%20to%20increase%20profit%2C%20the%20provision%20of%20tax%20holidays%20to%20induce%20investment%20and%20the%20acquisition%20of%20private%20land%20to%20be%20alloted%20to%20industry%20at%20a%20massive%20subsidy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20is%20done%20to%20the%20exclusion%20of%20social%20spending%2C%20winning%20the%20endorsement%20of%20the%20elite%20%E2%80%93%20the%20new%20middle%20class%20and%20dominant%20upper%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20latent%20%E2%80%9Cvalues%E2%80%9D%20have%20now%20become%20the%20primary%20ingredients%20of%20the%20magic%20formula%20for%20establishing%20a%20muscular%20Indian%20nation-state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20started%20its%20post-colonial%20journey%20as%20a%20constitutionally%20secular%20nation%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20building%20itself%20into%20a%20liberal%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20necessary%20institutions%20required%20for%20establishing%20a%20liberal%20democracy%20were%20duly%20established%20and%20nurtured%2C%20despite%20occasional%20aberrations%20and%20hiccups.However%2C%20India%20now%20seems%20to%20be%20turning%20to%20the%20right%2C%20just%20as%20many%20other%20powerful%20countries%20have%20done%20in%20the%2021st%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20rightward%20shift%20in%20India%20was%20aided%20by%20two%20inextricably%20linked%20transformations%3A%20an%20illiberal%20turn%20in%20Indian%20democracy%20and%20the%20rapid%20movement%20towards%20a%20neoliberal%20economic%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20happened%20while%20India%20has%20retained%20most%20of%20the%20formal%20representative%20institutions%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeoliberalism%20became%20the%20dominant%20public%20discourse%20globally%20and%20India%20too%20moved%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fcover-story%2Findian-neoliberalism-economic-reforms-at-30-a-toxic-gift-from-global-finance%2Farticle36290562.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eopen%20up%20its%20economy%20in%20the%20early%201990s%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20had%20two%20major%20consequences%20for%20Indian%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20under%20the%20spell%20of%20the%20neoliberal%20economy%2C%20almost%20all%20economic%20activities%20became%20subject%20to%20the%20market%2C%20to%20be%20assessed%20primarily%20in%20terms%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETemporary%20and%20market-based%20contracts%20displaced%20permanent%20arrangements%20in%20the%20economic%2C%20professional%2C%20cultural%20and%20political%20spheres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20neoliberal%20economy%20spelt%20utter%20disaster%20for%20the%20organised%20working%20class.%20In%20the%20formerly%20unionised%20or%20semi-unionised%20organised%20industrial%20sectors%2C%20workers%20were%20gradually%20disempowered%20by%20%C2%A0measures%20like%20the%20closure%20of%20industrial%20units%20or%20the%20expanded%20right%20to%20hire%20and%20fire%20through%20contractualisation%20of%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Indian%20economy%20opened%20up%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20there%20was%20discernible%2C%20although%20not%20consistent%2C%20movement%20towards%20creating%20a%20welfare%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20trade%20unions%20were%20strong%20in%20the%20public%20sector%20such%20as%20the%20railways%2C%20the%20banking%20sector%20and%20the%20insurance%20sector%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fwhen-nationalization-changed-the-face-of-indian-banking-from-class-to-mass-news-211018%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eespecially%20after%20their%20nationalisation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-unorganised-sector-is-being-engulfed-further-marginalised%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoverwhelming%20majority%20of%20the%20workforce%20was%20employed%20in%20the%20unorganised%20sector%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0like%20the%20construction%20industry.%20Not%20unionised%20and%20unprotected%20by%20laws%20as%20in%20the%20organised%20sector%2C%20it%20was%20unable%20to%20negotiate%20effectively%20with%20the%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20even%20in%20the%20regulated%20organised%20sector%2C%20the%20employees%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20in%20the%20emerging%20information%20technology%20and%20the%20communications%20sector%20%E2%80%93%20are%20unable%20to%20unionise%20for%20the%20fear%20of%20losing%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20emerging%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2Fcrowdwork-pitfalls-may-need-a-blockchain-reaction%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egig%20economy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20scope%20for%20forming%20unions%20is%20bleak%2C%20as%20most%20of%20the%20employees%20are%20casual%20or%20contractual%20workers.%20One%20of%20the%20results%20of%20the%20liberalisation%20of%20the%20economy%20was%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20middle%20class%20in%20metropolitan%20cities%20where%20quality%20education%20and%20better-paid%20jobs%20in%20service%20sectors%20were%20more%20easily%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20class%2C%20riding%20on%20the%20wave%20of%20neoliberalisation%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fedit-page%2Fleader-article-blame-the-middle-class%2Farticleshow%2F2681517.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%20in%20militant%20religious%20nationalism%20a%20new%20self-esteem%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20neoliberal%20economy%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20created%20more%20space%20for%20the%20politics%20of%20Hindutva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20primarily%20selling%20this%20ideology%2C%20has%20been%20effective%20in%20manufacturing%20consent%20through%20its%20cultivation%20of%20the%20emerging%20middle%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20middle%20class%20appreciates%20the%20pleasure%20of%20ownership%20of%20private%20property%2C%20gated%20communities%20and%20values%20of%20individualism%20above%20all%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20middle%20class%20and%20the%20echo%20chambers%20of%20the%20powers-that-be%20equally%20relish%20the%20close%20contacts%20and%20connections%20between%20the%20government%20and%20the%20captains%20of%20industry%20and%20finance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20frequently%20turns%20to%20these%20%E2%80%98captains%E2%80%99%20for%20advice%2C%20and%20delivers%20them%20favours%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inc.in%2Fcongress-sandesh%2Fcomment%2Fthe-distress-sale-of-national-assets-is-unwise%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eundervaluing%20state%20assets%20set%20for%20privatisation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20State%20subsidisation%20of%20capitalists%20and%20its%20active%20acceptance%20by%20the%20middle%20class%20has%20become%20the%20new%20norm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20developments%20have%20been%20accompanied%20by%20a%20growing%20judicialisation%20of%20administration.%20This%20implies%20a%20strong%20preference%20for%20governance%20by%20decree%2C%20executive%20fiat%20or%20by%20judicial%20decisions%20instead%20of%20democratic%2C%20participatory%2C%20deliberative%20and%20legislative%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20critical%20issues%20of%20policy-making%20were%20mostly%20being%20deliberated%20upon%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20national%20and%20state%20legislatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20now%20seems%20to%20prefer%20to%20tweak%20the%20legislative%20process%2C%20almost%20keeping%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20dark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExamples%20include%20overhauling%20the%20Indian%20Police%20Act%20or%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20of%20the%20colonial%20era%20by%20placing%20the%20bills%20without%20duly%20itemising%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20national%20legislature%2C%20or%20taking%20vital%20policy%20decisions%20when%20the%20Parliament%20is%20not%20in%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20and%20the%20new%20middle%20class%20look%20up%20more%20and%20more%20to%20the%20judiciary%20for%20remedy%20of%20any%20%E2%80%98%E2%80%98aberration%E2%80%99%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20administration%2C%20while%20the%20access%20to%20judiciary%20remains%20only%20nominally%20egalitarian%20and%20extremely%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20collaborate%20intimately%20with%20state%20actors%20and%20also%20have%20acquired%20a%20strong%20role%20in%20formulating%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20nexus%20brooks%20no%20criticism%2C%20so%20the%20regulatory%20framework%20favours%20corporations%2C%20rules%20are%20changed%20mid-game%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2023%2F3%2F1%2Fmodi-govt-allowed-adani-coal-deals-it-knew-were-inappropriate%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhich%20favour%20certain%20corporations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F1%2F26%2Fsurveillance-concerns-as-india-issues-new-digital-ids-in-kashmir%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enew%20forms%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20digital%20surveillance%20and%20policing%20of%20citizens%20multiply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20undermining%20of%20traditional%20practices%20and%20institutions%20makes%20homogenous%20Hindutva%20a%20dominant%20theme%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20comes%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20basic%20rights%20for%20religious%20and%20ethnic%20minorities%20and%20denies%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20multiple%20histories%20and%20multiple%20geographies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ESabyasachi%20Basu%20Ray%20Chaudhury%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20Professor%20of%20Political%20Science%20at%20Rabindra%20Bharati%20University%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20India.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Fli