%80%93%20Responsible%20for%20Polluting%20the%20Lake%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121541%2FPic-3.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDal%20Lake%2C%20located%20in%20the%20stunning%20Kashmir%20valley%2C%20has%20been%20recognised%20for%20a%20long%20time%20as%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20enchanting%20tourist%20spots.%20This%20serene%20sanctuary%20calls%20out%20to%20both%20domestic%20and%20international%20visitors%2C%20offering%20respite%20from%20the%20sweltering%20summer%20heat%20while%20showcasing%20the%20tranquil%20beauty%20of%20the%20area.%20However%2C%20recent%20developments%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20pollution%20and%20environmental%20impact%2C%20mainly%20pointing%20fingers%20at%20the%20cherished%20houseboats%20that%20lie%20anchored%20neatly%20in%20the%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20popularity%2C%20the%20houseboats%20have%20not%20been%20without%20controversy.%20Environmental%20activists%20and%20many%20researchers%20argue%20that%20these%20floating%20resorts%20are%20the%20main%20source%20of%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20pollution.%20In%20response%20to%20PILs%20that%20expressed%20concern%20for%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20well-being%2C%20the%20high%20court%20stepped%20in%20and%20imposed%20restrictions%2C%20capping%20the%20number%20of%20houseboats%20at%20700-900%20in%20Dal%20and%20Nigeen%20lakes%20and%20also%20advised%20shifting%20the%20excess%20houseboats%20to%20other%20water%20bodies%20in%20order%20to%20reduce%20pressure%20on%20the%20Dal.%20No%20new%20licenses%20were%20to%20be%20issued%2C%20and%20major%20repair%20work%20was%20also%20prohibited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20houseboat%20owners%20themselves%20reveal%20a%20tale%20of%20hardships%20and%20livelihoods%20under%20threat.%20The%20owners%20claim%20that%20the%20government%20is%20unfairly%20targeting%20their%20businesses%20since%20the%20actual%20sources%20of%20pollution%20lie%20in%20the%20catchment%20area%20compounded%20by%20poor%20governance%20and%20management%20by%20the%20lake%20authorities.%20A%20comprehensive%20study%20conducted%20by%20this%20author%20in%202018%20uncovered%20multiple%20enterprises%20operating%20on%20the%20lake%2C%20including%20tourism%20(houseboats%20and%20shikaras)%2C%20floating%20vegetable%20gardens%2C%20and%20fisheries.%20Being%20a%20common-use%20resource%2C%20conflicts%20inevitably%20arise%20while%20determining%20the%20optimal%20budgetary%20allocation%20and%20management%20priorities%20among%20competing%20stakeholders.%20Dal%20Lake%20has%20always%20been%20entangled%20in%20such%20conflicts%2C%20leading%20to%20an%20abysmally%20depressing%20situation%20in%20terms%20of%20sustainability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121623%2FHouboats-on-Dal-Lake-min.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121623%2FHouboats-on-Dal-Lake-min.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121623%2FHouboats-on-Dal-Lake-min-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121623%2FHouboats-on-Dal-Lake-min-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669738%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHouseboats%20on%20Dal%20Lake.%20Photo%3A%20Author%20provided%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20several%20instances%20of%20great%20lakes%20across%20the%20world%20like%20Lake%20Erie%20in%20North%20America%2C%20Lake%20Victoria%20in%20East%20Africa%20(the%20largest%20lake%20of%20Africa)%2C%20Taihu%20Lake%20of%20Eastern%20China%20and%20Constance%20Lake%20in%20Central%20Europe%20that%20have%20suffered%20from%20mismanagement%20of%20resources%20and%20have%20been%20revived%20successfully%20by%20implementing%20proper%20management%20strategies%2C%20international%20cooperation%20and%20community%20involvement.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20development%20and%20implementation%20of%20concerted%20co-management%20strategies%2C%20the%20influence%20of%20entrenched%20stakeholders%20with%20vested%20interests%20tend%20to%20overshadow%20the%20long-term%20welfare%20of%20the%20lake.%20Various%20government%20departments%20are%20responsible%20for%20the%20civic%20maintenance%20of%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Lake%20Conservation%20and%20Management%20Authority%20(LCMA)%2C%20Srinagar%20Municipal%20Corporation%20(SMC)%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20Tourism%20Department%2C%20revenue%2C%20electrical%2C%20agriculture%2C%20and%20the%20like.%20These%20departments%20allegedly%20engage%20in%20a%20blame%20game%2C%20avoiding%20responsibility%20for%20the%20abysmal%20state%20of%20the%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDal%20Lake%20needs%20to%20be%20operated%20at%20a%20compromised%20equilibrium%2C%20prioritising%20sustainability%20and%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20health%2C%20while%20allowing%20economic%20enterprises%20to%20flourish.%20The%20current%20level%20of%20pollution%20and%20hyper-eutrophication%20in%20Dal%20Lake%20has%20led%20many%20experts%20to%20declare%20it%20unsuitable%20for%20native%20fish%20species%2C%20such%20as%20snow%20trouts%2C%20which%20have%20been%20showing%20a%20constant%20decline%20in%20catches%20over%20the%20last%202-3%20decades.%20Many%20exotic%20hardy%20species%2C%20some%20introduced%20inadvertently%2C%20others%20by%20chance%20are%20proliferating%20in%20the%20polluted%20Dal%20waters%2C%20leading%20to%20an%20inevitable%20shift%20in%20consumer%20preferences%20due%20to%20the%20unavailability%20of%20indigenous%20species.%20However%2C%20reducing%20water%20pollution%20levels%20would%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20the%20native%20species%20to%20make%20a%20comeback.%20Contrary%20to%20popular%20belief%2C%20the%20declining%20catches%20of%20native%20species%20in%20the%20lake%20cannot%20be%20solely%20attributed%20to%20pollution%20levels%2C%20with%20houseboats%20often%20unfairly%20blamed%20as%20the%20primary%20source.%20However%2C%20the%20true%20reality%20unveils%20a%20different%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20houseboat%20generated%20net%20returns%20of%20Rs%201.47%20million%2C%20totalling%20Rs%201%2C109%20million%20for%20the%20750%20houseboats%20in%20the%20Dal%20Lake.%20These%20houseboats%20employ%203%2C525%20people%20annually%20of%20which%203%2C000%20were%20hired%20labour%20and%20525%20were%20accounted%20by%20family%20labour%20component.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20income%20generated%20by%20houseboats%20for%20hired%20labor%20worked%20out%20to%20be%20Rs%20250%20million.%20The%20pollution%20generated%20by%20total%20population%20living%20on%20the%20lake%20including%20the%20number%20of%20fisher%20families%2C%20vegetable%20farmers%2C%20houseboat%20inhabitants%20and%20tourists%20in%20houseboats%20has%20been%20estimated%20to%20be%20around%2033.82%20million%20litres%20of%20sewage%20which%20is%20very%20less%20compared%20to%20external%20untreated%20sewage%20flowing%20inside%20the%20lake%20(6587%20million%20litres%20per%20year).The%20houseboats%20if%20taken%20separately%20contribute%20only%206.3%20million%20litres%20of%20sewage%20which%20is%20less%20than%200.1%20%25%20of%20the%20total%20untreated%20sewage%20entering%20the%20lake%20system%20from%20the%20catchment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20houseboats%20operated%20at%20full%20capacity%20year-round%2C%20the%20increase%20in%20pollution%20load%20would%20be%20marginal%20(1.2%20million%20litres)%2C%20while%20doubling%20the%20revenue%20generated%20(Rs%202%2C200%20million).%20This%20finding%20puts%20paid%20to%20the%20notion%20that%20houseboats%20bear%20sole%20responsibility%20for%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20deteriorating%20water%20quality.%20Efforts%20should%20focus%20on%20restructuring%20the%20lopsided%20investments%20made%20in%20de-weeding%20and%20dredging%20the%20lake.%20The%20government%20budget%20(2017-18)%20for%20sewage%20treatment%20was%20Rs%203.4%20million.%20Outlays%20for%20dredging%20to%20remove%20excess%20silt%20from%20the%20lake%20was%20Rs%205%20million%20and%20for%20de-weeding%20to%20remove%20excessive%20growth%20of%20weeds%20was%20Rs%202.5%20million.%20There%20is%20a%20need%20to%20increase%20the%20investment%20in%20sewage%20treatment%20(making%20all%20STP%20units%20functional)%20while%20keeping%20other%20abatement%20measures%20unchanged%2C%20which%20could%20optimise%20pollution%20control%20in%20the%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121705%2FPic-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121705%2FPic-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121705%2FPic-2-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121705%2FPic-2-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669739%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHouseboats%20on%20Dal%20Lake.%20Photo%3A%20Author%20provided%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20faced%20by%20Dal%20Lake%20are%20a%20result%20of%20its%20inherent%20nature%20of%20being%20a%20common-use%20resource%20and%20the%20anthropogenic%20pressures%20that%20come%20with%20it.%20The%20rivalry%20in%20consumption%20and%20issues%20of%20excludability%20together%20in%20tandem%20create%20conflicts.%20Certain%20strategies%20for%20managing%20inter-stakeholder%20conflicts%20and%20sustainability%20issues%20include%20the%20consideration%20that%20while%20houseboats%20contribute%20significantly%20to%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20economic%20welfare%2C%20they%20occupy%20a%20considerable%20area%20that%20could%20otherwise%20be%20used%20for%20fishing.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20suggested%20that%20there%20should%20be%20a%20benefit%20transfer%20scheme%20mandated%20by%20government%20authorities%20under%20which%20a%20certain%20fixed%20portion%20of%20their%20profits%20or%20benefits%20can%20be%20directly%20transferred%20to%20local%20fishermen%20who%20are%20socio-economically%20weaker%20and%20more%20vulnerable%20than%20other%20stakeholders%20of%20the%20lake.%20Additionally%2C%20solid%20waste%20and%20non-biodegradable%20waste%20from%20houseboats%20should%20be%20collected%20daily%20by%20the%20houseboat%20operators%20and%20deposited%20in%20a%20designated%20place%20where%20the%20waste%20should%20be%20assessed%20by%20weight%20and%20volume%20which%20may%20be%20incentivised%20by%20the%20government%20with%20green%20credits%20which%20could%20be%20encased%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20This%20will%20help%20in%20preventing%20its%20direct%20disposal%20into%20the%20water.%20License%20fees%20for%20houseboats%20could%20also%20be%20reviewed%20periodically.%20This%20must%20be%20contingent%20upon%20implementing%20eco-friendly%20practices%2C%20responsible%20waste%20management%20and%20promoting%20environmentally%20conscious%20tourism.%20To%20encourage%20best%20practices%2C%20healthy%20competition%20among%20houseboats%20based%20on%20various%20parameters%20could%20be%20fostered%2C%20with%20awards%20and%20incentives%20given%20to%20top%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20untreated%20sewage%20inflow%20from%20the%20catchment%20needs%20to%20be%20regulated%20and%20treated%20properly.%20Although%20there%20are%20already%20five%20STPs%20installed%20along%20the%20catchment%20of%20the%20lake%2C%20only%20three%20are%20functional.%20Therefore%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20install%20more%20STPs%20and%20divert%20investments%20toward%20this%20cause.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20newly%20installed%20STPs%20are%20properly%20designed%2C%20constructed%20and%20operated%20to%20meet%20the%20required%20standards%20for%20sewage%20treatment.%20Regular%20maintenance%20and%20monitoring%20should%20also%20be%20carried%20out%20to%20ensure%20their%20long-term%20functionality.%20In%20addition%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20implement%20measures%20aimed%20at%20reducing%20the%20volume%20of%20untreated%20sewage%20entering%20the%20lake.%20The%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Abhiyan%20has%20ensured%20the%20availability%20of%20public%20toilets%20which%20must%20be%20put%20to%20best%20use%20and%20its%20use%20promoted%20among%20the%20local%20people%2C%20driving%20home%20the%20benefits%20of%20a%20clean%20environment.%20Environmental%20activists%20and%20approved%20NGOs%20can%20engage%20in%20organising%20cleanup%20drives%2C%20and%20community%20education%20and%20advocate%20for%20pushing%20the%20agenda%20of%20conserving%20and%20delivering%20a%20lovelier%20Dal%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EData%20and%20values%20from%20Qureshi%20(2018)%20PhD%20Thesis%20on%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Amplified%20Economics%20of%20an%20Intrinsic%20Common%20Use%20Resource%3A%20The%20Dal%20Lake%E2%80%9D%20available%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkrishikosh.egranth.ac.in%2Fhandle%2F1%2F5810154517%5C%22%3EKrishikosh%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENeha%20Wajahat%20Qureshi%20is%20a%20scientist%20at%20ICAR-Central%20Institute%20of%20Fisheries%20Education%2C%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693013436000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25121541%2FPic-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fhouseboats-on-srinagars-dal-arent-solely-or-even-primarily-responsible-for-polluting-the-lake%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20houseboats%20contribute%20only%206.3%20million%20litres%20of%20sewage%2C%20which%20is%20less%20than%200.1%25%20of%20the%20total%20untreated%2