r%2C%20the%20focus%20of%20this%20work%20is%20on%20the%20genesis%20or%20sources%20of%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20political%20thought%20and%20its%20evolution%20during%20the%20most%20turbulent%20period%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20democratisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhattacharjee%20outlines%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20personal%20and%20political%20career%20with%20numerous%20references%2C%20most%20of%20which%20includes%20India%E2%80%99s%20social%20and%20political%20developments%20before%20and%20after%20independence.%20For%20Nehru%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20dedicated%20freedom%20fighters%20whose%20life%20and%20impact%20extended%20not%20only%20to%20the%20long%20incubation%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20but%20also%20%E2%80%93%20and%20more%20importantly%20%E2%80%93%20to%20a%20considerably%20long%20post-independence%20phase%20in%20which%2C%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20prime%20minister%2C%20he%20played%20a%20decisive%20role%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20free%20and%20democratic%20India%20until%20his%20death%20in%201964.%20Nonetheless%2C%20the%20leitmotif%20of%20this%20work%20by%20Bhattacharjee%20is%20not%20a%20conventional%20historical-political%20contextualisation%20of%20Nehru%20in%20the%20independence%20struggle%20and%20the%20post-independence%20politics%20of%20modernising%20India.%20Rather%2C%20it%20clearly%20highlights%20and%20establishes%20Nehru%20as%20a%20political%20thinker%2C%20whose%20influence%20far%20surpasses%20his%20life%20as%20a%20freedom%20fighter%20and%20later%20as%20a%20statesman%20and%20architect%20of%20modern%20India.%20The%20inundation%20of%20historical-political%20sketching%20of%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20life%20so%20far%20seems%20to%20overshadow%20any%20examination%20of%20the%20genesis%2C%20sources%20as%20well%20as%20unfolding%20of%20his%20philosophical%20and%20political%20thought.%20Bhattacharjee%20attempts%20to%20contextualise%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20influence%20as%20statesman-politician%20of%20post-independence%20India%20through%20his%20political%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20this%20perspective%2C%20the%20fundamental%20problem%20that%20Nehru%20confronted%20throughout%20his%20life%20and%20in%20his%20political%20thinking%20about%20India%20%E2%80%93%20its%20history%2C%20traditions%20and%20cultural%20diversity%20%E2%80%93%20can%20be%20identified%20as%20the%20incessant%20reflection%20on%20%E2%80%98identity%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20Bhattacharjee%20convincingly%20points%20out%20and%20discusses%20in%20depth.%20The%20two%20important%20chapters%20in%20this%20work%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Citizen%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Secular%20State%20Business%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ECulture%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Urge%20towards%20Synthesis%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20refer%20to%2C%20even%20build%20on%2C%20this%20basic%20problematic%2C%20which%2C%20along%20with%20many%20other%20ethnically%20more%20homogeneous%20nations%20and%20civilisations%20on%20earth%20strangely%20engulfs%20India%20too.%20(Accordingly%2C%20the%20contrast%20between%20ethnic%20and%20civic%20nationalism%2C%20or%20national%20identity%2C%20constitutes%20an%20important%20point%20in%20this%20study).%20The%20sources%20of%20the%20radical%20polemic%20against%20the%20commonly%20thought%20%E2%80%98principle%20of%20identity%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20has%20been%20handed%20down%20in%20the%20history%20of%20philosophy%2C%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20the%20foundations%20of%20Western%20philosophical%20logic.%20The%20part%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EI%20is%20not%20Identity%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20chapter%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Citizen%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20the%20%E2%80%98Secular%20State%20Business%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20introduces%20the%20central%20polemic%20against%20the%20principle%20of%20identity%20within%20the%20theoretical-philosophical%20framework%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIdentity%20is%20not%20identical%20to%20itself.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20we%20are%20not%20identical%20to%20our%20identity.%20Every%20identity%20is%20a%20secret%3A%20of%20being%20bit%20other%20to%20itself.%20Arthur%20Rimbaud%20famously%20declared%20in%20a%20letter%20written%20in%201871%20to%20his%20friend%20and%20minor%20poet%20Paul%20Demeny%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98I%20is%20other%E2%80%99.%20If%20I%20may%20extend%20the%20proposition%3A%20%3Cem%3EI%20is%20not%20identity.%20I%20is%20not%20identical%20to%20itself.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EI%20is%2Fam%20another%20%E2%80%93%20both%20as%20experience%20and%20possibility.%20You%20can%E2%80%99t%20fully%20claim%20to%20be%20just%20one%20thing%2C%20and%20not%20the%20other%20thing.%20Identity%20is%20not%20a%20definition%2C%20but%20a%20tendency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20philosophical%20logic%2C%20the%20proposition%20of%20identity%20is%20a%20fundamental%20principle%20that%20cannot%20be%20reduced%20as%20such.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20principle%20of%20identity%20is%20represented%20abstractly%20as%20%3Cem%3EA%20%3D%20A%3C%2Fem%3E.%20As%20a%20fundamental%20principle%20of%20logic%20it%20cannot%20suffer%20any%20contradiction.%20In%20his%20major%20work%2C%20%3Cem%3EPhenomenology%20of%20Knowledge%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Ph%C3%A4nomenologie%20der%20Erkenntnis)%2C%20philosopher%20Ernst%20Cassirer%20problematises%20afresh%20this%20irrefutable%20and%20irreducible%20proposition%20of%20identity%20in%20philosophical%20logic.%20Cassirer%20quotes%20the%20above-mentioned%20logical%20principle%20of%20identity%2C%20and%20asks%3A%20But%20what%20is%20A%3F%20It%20is%20clearly%20an%20ontological%20question%20that%20refers%20to%20the%20existential%20status%20of%20%E2%80%98A%E2%80%99%20as%20a%20mere%20abstract%20entity.%20Cassirer%E2%80%99s%20polemic%20indicates%20that%20the%20logical%20principle%20of%20identity%20equates%20arbitrarily%20only%20the%20abstract%20entities%20with%20each%20other%2C%20which%2C%20as%20such%2C%20cannot%20%E2%80%98exist%E2%80%99.%20If%20A%20is%20a%20concrete%20entity%20%E2%80%93%20like%20a%20material%20thing%20%E2%80%93%20it%20becomes%20more%20difficult%2C%20even%20impossible%2C%20to%20equate%20A%20with%20A.%20This%20is%20because%20reality%20in%20concreteness%20is%20subject%20to%20the%20spatio-temporal%20framework%2C%20which%20transcends%20an%20abstract%20principle%20of%20identity.%20The%20prime%20example%20of%20this%20would%20be%20the%20famous%20dictum%20of%20Heraclitus%20%E2%80%93%20the%20pre-Socratic%20philosopher%20of%20%E2%80%98becoming%20and%20change%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20same%20river%20cannot%20be%20trodden%20twice.%20Even%20more%20ingenious%20is%20the%20extension%20of%20this%20Heraclitian%20observation%20by%20Cratylus%20that%20the%20same%20river%20cannot%20be%20trodden%20even%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20287px)%2085vw%2C%20287px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16155825%2F61lu2rEROgL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22287%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16155825%2F61lu2rEROgL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20623w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16155825%2F61lu2rEROgL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-187x300.jpg%20187w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-658584%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22461%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EManash%20Firaq%20Bhattacharjee%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ENehru%20and%20the%20Spirit%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPenguin%2C%202022%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20political%20level%2C%20this%20impossibility%20of%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20same%20entity%20in%20concretion%20could%20be%20expressed%20as%20follows%3A%20Absolute%20identity%2C%20which%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20a%20contradiction%2C%20is%20based%20on%20a%20mere%20abstract%2C%20i.e.%2C%20an%20abstract%20idea%20of%20existence%2C%20and%20can%20therefore%20only%20be%20imagined%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20%E2%80%98ideal%E2%80%99%20politics.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20concretion%20or%20concretisation%20of%20the%20abstract%2C%20on%20which%20%E2%80%98real%E2%80%99%20politics%20is%20based%2C%20leads%20to%20an%20identity%20that%20is%20not%20an%20identity%20in%20itself%2C%20but%20an%20identity%20with%20the%20non-identical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20non-identical%20or%20the%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20in%20this%20principle%20of%20identity%20in%20concretion%20clearly%20states%2C%20as%20Bhattacharjee%20emphasises%2C%20that%20identity%20is%20not%20a%20definition%20but%20a%20tendency.%20In%20other%20words%3A%20Identity%20is%20not%20a%20final%20state%20or%20a%20finality%20that%20presupposes%20both%20the%20existential%20finality%20of%20the%20identical%20and%20its%20final%20knowability.%20The%20non-identical%20in%20identity%20generates%20a%20rather%20dynamic%20tendency%20towards%20identity%20that%20bursts%20every%20limit%20of%20%3Cem%3Edefinition%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20finality%20of%20abstract%20ideas%20%E2%80%93%20to%20culminate%20in%20an%20infinity%20of%20cognition%20and%20knowability.%20In%20%3Cem%3ETotality%20and%20Infinity%3A%20An%20Essay%20on%20Exteriority%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Emmanuel%20Levinas%20(a%20major%2020th%20century%20philosopher%2C%20referred%20to%20several%20times%20in%20Bhattacharjee%E2%80%99s%20work)%20points%20to%20the%20infinity%20of%20the%20face%20of%20the%20other%20%E2%80%93%20in%20its%20exteriority%20and%20knowability.%20The%20infinity%20of%20the%20face%2C%20which%20always%20prevents%20a%20final%20or%20definable%20cognisability%20of%20the%20other%2C%20seems%20to%20suggest%20here%20an%20infinite%20tendency%20towards%20identity%20with%20the%20other.%20Another%20prime%20example%20from%20the%20history%20of%20philosophy%2C%20in%20which%20such%20an%20infinite-processual%20tendency%20towards%20identity%20comes%20to%20light%2C%20would%20be%20the%20doctrine%20of%20%3Cem%3Econcidentia%20oppositorum%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Cusanus%20(Nicholas%20of%20Cusa)%2C%20a%20prominent%20Neo-Platonist%20of%20the%20late%20Middle%20Ages.%20In%20this%20doctrine%20of%20Cusanus%2C%20a%20static%20and%20final%20identity%20of%20the%20same%20is%20imagined%20through%20an%20infinite%20tendency%20of%20even%20opposite%20entities%20to%20coincidence%20or%20identity%20in%20oneness.%20In%20his%20major%20works%20%3Cem%3EDe%20docta%20ignorantia%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EDe%20coniecturis%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Cusanus%20shows%20the%20infinite%20tendency%20of%20opposites%20to%20coincide%20in%20the%20identical%20by%20means%20of%20a%20few%20geometrical%20thought%20experiments.%20Eg%3A%20the%20curved%20periphery%20of%20an%20infinitely%20enlarging%20circle%20that%20tends%20infinitely%20towards%20an%20identity%20with%20the%20linear%20tangent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20way%2C%20the%20proposition%20of%20identity%2C%20on%20which%20the%20history%20of%20philosophical%2C%20mathematical%20and%20scientific%20logic%20and%20the%20human%20sciences%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20politics%2C%20sociology%2C%20ethnology%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20built%2C%20was%20already%20questioned%20in%20classical%20antiquity%20and%20medieval%20Neo-Platonism.%20Modernity%2C%20as%20we%20know%2C%20is%20confronted%20with%20problems%20and%20anomalies%20that%20the%20long-established%20notion%20of%20identity%20has%20prompted%20to%20emerge%20in%20history%2C%20as%20Bhattacharjee%20convincingly%20discusses.%20The%20most%20significant%20of%20these%20problems%20would%20be%20the%20myth%20of%20totality%2C%20which%20results%20in%20the%20rather%20ideal%20and%20abstractly%20imagined%20homogeneous%20identity%3A%20%E2%80%9CSince%20identity%20is%20not%20identical%20to%20itself%2C%20it%20is%20also%20not%20identical%20to%20totality.%20That%20is%20why%20identity%20politics%20breaks%20the%20norm%20of%20(majoritarian)%20consensus.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20clearly%20suggests%20that%20majoritarian%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20or%20politics%20of%20totality%20%E2%80%93%20arises%20from%20an%20inadequate%2C%20even%20flawed%2C%20notion%20of%20absolute%20identity.%20The%20cultural-political%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20excluded%20from%20the%20national%2C%20majoritarian%20identity%2C%20as%20represented%20particularly%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20predetermination%20of%20citizenship%2C%20is%20based%20on%20a%20false%20notion%20of%20identity%20in%20its%20%3Cem%3Eabstract%20finality%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Identity%20as%20a%20tendency%20therefore%20accommodates%20the%20other%20in%20the%20identical%2C%20which%20is%20not%20imagined%20in%20mere%20abstraction%2C%20but%20experienced%20as%20real%20and%20concrete.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20identity%20appears%20at%20various%20points%20in%20Bhattacharjee%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20different%20contexts.%20One%20of%20them%20is%20%3Cem%3EParadoxes%20of%20Identity%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20discussed%20in%20the%20chapter%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Citizen%20and%20the%20Secular%20State%20of%20Business%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20paradoxes%20of%20identity%20are%20based%20on%20the%20above-mentioned%20contradictory%20fact%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%9D%20is%20not%20identical%20with%20the%20same%2C%20that%20the%20very%20principle%20of%20identity%20transcends%20the%20oneness%20and%20presupposes%20the%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99.%20To%20introduce%20and%20explicate%20this%20paradox%2C%20Bhattacharjee%20quotes%20the%20Spanish%20poet%20Antonio%20Machado%20who%20emphasises%20the%20inevitable%20persistence%20of%20the%20other%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20%3Cem%3Eother%20%3C%2Fem%3Edoes%20not%20exist%3A%20this%20is%20rational%20faith%2C%20the%20incurable%20belief%20of%20human%20reason.%20Identity%3DReality%2C%20as%20if%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20everything%20must%20necessarily%20and%20absolutely%20be%20%3Cem%3Eone%20and%20the%20same%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20the%20other%20refuses%20to%20disappear%3B%20it%20subsists%2C%20it%20persists%2C%20it%20is%20the%20hard%20bone%20on%20which%20reason%20breaks%20its%20teeth.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20discourse%20leads%20to%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20findings%20in%20Bhattacharjee%E2%80%99s%20study%2C%20that%20the%20common%20and%20prevailing%20principle%20of%20identity%2C%20namely%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20self%20or%20subject%20with%20itself%2C%20nurtures%20the%20majoritarianism%20or%20totalitarianism%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98majority%E2%80%99%3A%20%E2%80%9CMajoritarianism%20is%20identity%20that%20identifies%20itself%20completely%20with%20totality.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98minorities%E2%80%99%20are%20hardly%20exempt%20from%20such%20totalitarianism%20of%20majoritarianism%20as%20long%20as%20they%20ethnically%20and%20religiously%20%C2%A0%E2%80%98identify%E2%80%99%20with%20themselves%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20common%20or%20conventional%20identity%20principle.%20This%20clearly%20points%20to%20a%20paradox%20of%20identity.%20Bhattacharjee%20observes%20that%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20own%20identity%20was%20hardly%20liberated%20from%20the%20paradoxes%20of%20identity.%20%E2%80%9CIdentity%20also%20creates%20paradoxes.%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20own%20identity%20was%20no%20exception%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20is%20well%20known%2C%20Nehru%20was%20accused%20of%20non-belonging%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20or%20even%20foreigner%20by%20the%20Hindu%20majoritarianism%2C%20especially%20propagated%20by%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%2C%20because%20of%20his%20Western%20education%20and%20Persian%20heritage.%20The%20intrinsic%20otherness%20or%20foreignness%2C%20as%20Bhattacharjee%20observes%2C%20contributes%20to%20or%20enhances%20the%20%E2%80%98identity%E2%80%99%20in%20Indian%20history%20and%20politics.%20For%2C%20%E2%80%9Cidentity%20breaks%20all%20ideas%20of%20oneness%20into%20two%E2%80%9D.%20Moreover%2C%20Persia%20has%20been%20an%20integral%20factum%20of%20Indian%20culture%20for%20millennia%2C%20inherent%20and%20persistent%20in%20languages%20and%20in%20various%20facets%20of%20Indian%20traditions%20and%20everyday%20life.%20This%20seems%20to%20suggest%20that%20identity%20also%20goes%20beyond%20twoness%20%E2%80%93%20as%20I%20and%20other%20%E2%80%93%20to%20build%20on%20many%20layers%20of%20%E2%80%98identities%E2%80%99%20represented%20in%20historical%20%E2%80%98heritages%E2%80%99%20and%20cultural%20practices.%20Identity%20incorporates%20several%20particulars%20within%20itself%2C%20but%20they%20hardly%20constitute%20a%20universal%2C%20i.e.%2C%20a%20universal%20idea.%20%E2%80%9CIdentity%20is%20not%20universal%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-relook-at-jawaharlal-nehru%5C%22%3EA%20Relook%20at%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20the%20old%20philosophical%20problem%2C%20namely%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20belonging%20or%20participation%20of%20the%20particular%20in%20the%20universal%2C%20seems%20to%20reappear.%20In%20%3Cem%3Ereal%20politics%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20particular%20refers%20to%20all%20individual%20identities%2C%20which%20in%20principle%20cannot%20be%20subsumed%20under%20a%20unified%20universal%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20whole.%20In%20the%20real-political%20framework%2C%20such%20universals%20tacitly%20lead%20to%20totalitarianism.%20For%20the%20whole%20here%2C%20even%20though%20it%20gives%20the%20appearance%20of%20unity%20and%20universality%2C%20ultimately%20implies%20the%20totality%20under%20which%20the%20individual%20identities%20are%20buried.%20The%20particular%20identities%20are%20clearly%20all%20other%20groups%20of%20peoples%20who%20are%20outside%20the%20majority%20or%20majoritarian%20identity%2C%20such%20as%20Dalits%2C%20religious%20minorities%2C%20migrants%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20How%20should%20the%20particular%20participate%20as%20a%20part%20in%20the%20whole%20that%20seemingly%20forms%20a%20general%20identity%3F%20If%20identity%20is%20neither%20unitary%20nor%20universal%20(as%20Bhattacharjee%20points%20out)%2C%20the%20participation%20of%20particular%20parts%20in%20a%20general%20whole%20proves%20to%20be%20problematic%2C%20as%20it%20leads%20to%20a%20hierarchical%20order%20in%20which%20the%20particulars%20are%20subordinated%20to%20the%20general%20or%20universal.%20The%20problem%20of%20the%20participation%20of%20particulars%20or%20particular%20parts%20in%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20whole%20was%20famously%20introduced%20and%20discussed%20in%20detail%20in%20%3Cem%3EParmenides%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20of%20Plato%E2%80%99s%20middle%20dialogues.%20Interestingly%2C%20this%20dialectical%20attempt%20for%20a%20solution%20ends%20in%20a%20hopeless%20riddle%2C%20i.e.%2C%20characteristically%20in%20aporia.%5Bfootntoe%5DPlato%3A%20%3Cem%3EParmenides%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%3A%20Plato.%20Complete%20Works%2C%20ed.%20John%20M.%20Cooper%2C%20Hackett%20Publishing%20Company%2C%20Indianapolis%2C%20p.%20366%20(132a-b)%5B%2Ffootnote%5D%C2%A0The%20participation%20of%20the%20particular%20parts%20in%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20whole%2C%20which%20found%20no%20solution%20in%20Platonic%20philosophy%2C%20seems%20to%20resurface%20after%20two%20millennia.%20The%20independence%20struggle%20in%20the%20early%20decades%20of%20the%2020th%20century%20also%20witnessed%20constitutional%20debates%20on%20the%20belongingness%20and%20autonomy%20of%20the%20minorities%20and%20the%20marginalised%20Dalits%20in%20their%20participation%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98whole%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20clearly%20points%20to%20a%20totalitarian%20identity.%20In%20the%20Bombay%20Legislative%20Assembly%20held%20on%20October%2027%2C%201939%2C%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20author%20of%20the%20Indian%20Democratic%20Constitution%2C%20was%20to%20polemicise%20fiercely%20against%20the%20hierarchical%20subsumption%20of%20the%20particular%20sections%20of%20the%20population%2C%20especially%20Dalits%2C%20under%20a%20majoritarian%20identity%2C%20while%20arguing%20passionately%20for%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98parts%E2%80%99%20that%20signify%20the%20autonomy%20and%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20historically%20oppressed%20Dalits.%20In%20the%20real-political%20framework%2C%20the%20ancient%20Platonic%20aporia%20resurfaces%20when%20Ambedkar%20establishes%20the%20parts%20not%20as%20mere%20particulars%20participating%20in%20an%20overarching%20whole%2C%20but%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpart%20apart%E2%80%9D%20or%20parts%20in%20their%20existential%20autonomy%20and%20sovereignty.%20Bhattacharjee%20excellently%20explicates%20how%20this%20historically%20persistent%20aporia%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20participation%20of%20the%20parts%20in%20the%20whole%20%E2%80%93%20can%20emerge%20from%20the%20universalization%20of%20identity%20by%20means%20of%20unification%20and%20logification.%20Here%2C%20the%20real%20is%20not%20congruent%20with%20the%20speculative%20logical-ideal%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20B.G.%20Kher%20argued%20with%20Ambedkar%20that%20he%20can%E2%80%99t%20hold%20that%20the%20depressed%20classes%20have%20%E2%80%98precedence%E2%80%99%20over%20the%20country%20as%20%E2%80%98the%20part%20can%20never%20be%20greater%20than%20the%20whole%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20latter%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20am%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20whole%3B%20I%20am%20a%20part%20apart.%E2%80%99%20Ambedkar%20makes%20the%20point%20brilliantly%20that%20if%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20whole%20lies%20in%20being%20whole%2C%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20part%20in%20being%20a%2Fpart.%20The%20subtractive%20is%20as%20crucial%20for%20the%20whole%20as%20the%20additive.%20It%20is%20only%20through%20twoness%20that%20oneness%20is%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Nehru%20was%20socio-politically%20obsessed%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20unity%2C%20which%2C%20as%20Bhattacharjee%20observes%2C%20explicates%20his%20fundamental%20inclination%20towards%20totality.%20Nehru%20was%20sceptical%20of%20the%20majoritarian%20tendency%20of%20minorities%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20arises%20from%20the%20prevailing%20notion%20of%20identity.%20After%20all%2C%20Nehru%20passionately%20pleaded%20for%20%E2%80%9Cunity%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cunity%20in%20diversity%E2%80%9D%2C%20wherein%20a%20tendency%20to%20%E2%80%9Csecular%20majoritarianism%E2%80%9D%20can%20be%20discerned%2C%20as%20Bhattacharjee%20diagnoses%20it.%20It%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20here%20that%20it%20is%20actually%20the%20%3Cem%3Elegitimate%3C%2Fem%3E%20reversal%20of%20this%20famous%20motto%20of%20modern%20Indian%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20in%20a%20theoretical-philosophical%20framework%20%E2%80%93%20that%20best%20corresponds%20to%20the%20above-discussed%20intrinsic%20heterogeneity%20of%20identity.%20Accordingly%2C%20the%20basic%20%E2%80%9Cdemocratic%E2%80%9D%20notion%20of%20%E2%80%9Cunity%20in%20diversity%E2%80%9D%20can%20be%20turned%20around%20into%20the%20notion%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdiversity%20in%20unity%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20privileges%20diversity%20as%20a%20precondition%20of%20unity%20and%20can%20also%20dignify%20and%20legitimise%20the%20paradoxes%20of%20Identity%20outlined%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20twoness%20or%20multi-layeredness%20inherent%20in%20identity%20also%20explains%20the%20ambivalence%20in%20belonging%20to%20a%20culture%20that%20embodies%20a%20heterogeneous%20genesis%20and%20historicity.%20Cultural%20belonging%20emerges%20from%20a%20complex%20constellation%20of%20predetermined%20and%20chosen%20sources%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%20believed%20in%20a%20rationalist%20self%20(with%20an%20%E2%80%98anchor%20of%20precise%20objective%20knowledge%20tested%20by%20reason%E2%80%99).%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20his%20cultural%20identity%2C%20the%20question%20of%20belonging%20is%20inevitably%20paramount.%20Belonging%20is%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20choice.%20In%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20case%20it%20is%20partly%20%3Cem%3Ealready%20chosen%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20his%20ancestry.%20Nehru%20can%E2%80%99t%20free%20himself%2C%20as%20he%20wrote%2C%20from%20%E2%80%98past%20inheritance%20or%20my%20recent%20acquisitions%E2%80%99.%20Identity%20is%20a%20paradox%20and%20just%20like%20modernity%2C%20it%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20interpretation.%20They%20are%20both%20narratives%20of%20experience%20and%20imagination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20ambivalent%20affiliations%20underlie%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20and%20political%20outsiderness%2C%20they%20also%20formed%20a%20legitimate%20background%2C%20justified%20by%20the%20heterogeneity%20and%20paradoxes%20inherent%20in%20identity%20itself.%20The%20outsider%20or%20outsider%20identity%20that%20always%20accompanied%20Nehru%20in%20his%20life%20and%20politics%2C%20and%20from%20which%20he%20could%20not%20detach%20himself%2C%20has%20in%20the%20present%20become%20an%20accusation%20of%20his%20cultural%20and%20political%20non-belonging.%20Bhattacharjee%20quotes%20from%20%3Cem%3EAn%20Autobiography%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20famous%20confession%20of%20Nehru%2C%20in%20which%20he%20expresses%20his%20diremption%20or%20state%20of%20being%20torn%20between%20East%20and%20West%20as%20well%20as%20his%20incessant%20foreignness%20and%20exile%20in%20both%20cultural%20spaces%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20often%20wonder%20if%20I%20represent%20anyone%20at%20all%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20have%20become%20a%20queer%20mixture%20of%20the%20East%20and%20the%20West%2C%20out%20of%20place%20everywhere%2C%20at%20home%20nowhere.%20Perhaps%20my%20thoughts%20and%20approach%20to%20life%20are%20more%20akin%20to%20what%20is%20called%20Western%20than%20Eastern%2C%20but%20India%20clings%20to%20me%2C%20as%20she%20does%20to%20all%20her%20children%2C%20in%20innumerable%20ways%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20can%20not%20get%20rid%20of%20either%20that%20past%20inheritance%20or%20my%20recent%20acquisitions%20%E2%80%A6%20They%20create%20in%20me%20a%20spiritual%20loneliness%20not%20only%20in%20public%20activities%20but%20in%20life%20itself.%20I%20am%20a%20stranger%20and%20alien%20in%20the%20West%20%E2%80%A6%20But%20in%20my%20own%20country%20also%2C%20sometimes%2C%20I%20have%20an%20exile%E2%80%99s%20feeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20appropriate%20references%2C%20Bhattacharjee%20shows%20the%20ambivalence%20in%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20identity%20as%20%3Cem%3Eunheimlich%3C%2Fem%3E%20(uncanny)%20or%20being%20homeless%20in%20the%20consciousness%20of%20a%20double%20modernity%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%20emerges%20as%20a%20man%20of%20double%20modernity.%20This%20doubleness%20of%20identity%20across%20two%20or%20more%20cultures%20makes%20Nehru%20an%20exemplary%20figure.%20The%20relationship%20with%20Europe%20would%20have%20been%20modern%20in%20an%20intellectual%20but%20not%20experiential%20way.%20Nehru%20did%20not%20have%20to%20go%20through%20any%20crisis%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20Christianity.%20In%20India%2C%20however%2C%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20identity%20mirrored%20an%20impressive%20heterogeneity.%20(%E2%80%A6)%20The%20man%20who%20lived%20a%20double%20modernity%20suffered%20in%20his%20own%20admission%20%E2%80%93%20a%20sense%20of%20cultural%20homelessness%20that%20we%20may%20describe%20as%20spiritual%20%3Cem%3Eunheimlich%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParadoxically%2C%20if%20Nehru%20is%20accused%20of%20cultural%20disaffiliation%20because%20of%20this%20intrinsic%20and%20cultivated%20outsiderness%20in%20life%20and%20politics%2C%20he%20is%20now%20consolidating%20more%20and%20more%20his%20cultural%20and%20political%20belonging%20%E2%80%93%20not%20merely%20in%20the%20Indian%20but%20in%20the%20universal%20framework%20of%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20as%20Bhattacharjee%E2%80%99s%20investigation%20seems%20to%20imply.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20political%20and%20cultural%20identity%20and%20belonging%20prima%20facie%20presuppose%20cultural%20and%20political%20insidership%20which%20is%20structurally%20more%20or%20less%20homogeneous.%20In%20politics%2C%20everyone%20strives%20to%20become%20an%20insider.%20One%20may%20ask%2C%20whether%20being%20a%20cultural-political%20outsider%20even%20has%20an%20identity%20and%20belonging%20that%20the%20culture%20and%20politics%20of%20a%20nation%20would%20require%3F%20Which%20central%20role%20can%20a%20cultural-political%20outsider%20play%20in%20real%20politics%3F%20Apparently%2C%20the%20disinterest%20in%20power%20as%20determined%20by%20Plato%20clearly%20points%20to%20a%20certain%20outsider-status%20of%20the%20statesman%20and%20hence%20to%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20his%20political%20existence%20and%20cultural%20belonging.%20For%20political%20insiders%20are%20commonly%20characterised%20by%20an%20incessant%20interest%20in%20political%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20Plato%E2%80%99s%20legitimisation%2C%20this%20exceptional%20status%20and%20identity%20of%20the%20outsider%20seems%20to%20have%20some%20positive%20effects%20in%20real%20politics.%20It%20is%20ultimately%20the%20political%20insider%20who%20is%20excluded%20of%20a%20homogeneous%20political%20identity%20and%20belonging.%20In%20contrast%2C%20a%20cultural%20and%20political%20outsider%20cannot%20be%20excluded%20from%20cultural%20belonging%20or%20politics.%20For%20it%20is%20a%20logical%20impossibility%20that%20an%20outsider%2C%20who%20is%20already%20outside%20a%20system%2C%20will%20be%20excluded%20again.%20As%20is%20known%2C%20it%20is%20rather%20from%20an%20outsider%E2%80%99s%20perspective%2C%20which%20requires%20a%20universal%20rather%20than%20a%20national%20point%20of%20view%2C%20that%20a%20nation%2C%20i.e.%2C%20its%20cultural%20past%20and%20present%20legitimacy%20in%20world%20politics%20is%20better%20understood%20than%20an%20insider%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20which%20cannot%20free%20itself%20from%20the%20deceptive%20spell%20of%20particularism.%20Moreover%2C%20any%20strategic%20endeavour%20to%20culturally%20and%20politically%20exclude%20an%20outsider%20%E2%80%93%20who%2C%20in%20certain%20sense%2C%20is%20closer%20to%20Plato%E2%80%99s%20statesman%20%E2%80%93%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20contradictory%20or%20dialectical%20outcome%20that%20the%20outsider%20becomes%20more%20and%20more%20an%20insider.%20This%20is%20astonishingly%20evidenced%20in%20our%20present%20time%20by%20the%20ever-increasing%20studies%20on%20Pundit%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20his%20unparalleled%20historical-political%20impact%20and%20relevance%2C%20to%20which%20Bhattacharjee%E2%80%99s%20work%20contributes%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%2C%20however%2C%20was%20not%20uninterested%20in%20political%20power%2C%20the%20maintenance%20of%20which%20he%20considered%20a%20responsibility%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20This%20also%20corresponds%20to%20his%20statesmanlike%20status%20%E2%80%93%20as%20Plato%20defines%20it.%20The%20interest%20in%20power%20from%20a%20statesman%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%20unfolded%20in%20Nehru%20as%20a%20continuation%20of%20his%20quest%20for%20the%20discovery%20of%20a%20nation%20and%20civilisation%20%E2%80%93%20a%20quest%20which%20Nehru%20maintained%20throughout%20his%20life%20and%20which%20also%20constituted%20an%20important%20and%20highly%20distinctive%20chapter%20in%20his%20%3Cem%3EDiscovery%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20quest%20now%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20dimensioned%20by%20some%20of%20the%20facts%20highlighted%20by%20Bhattacharjee%2C%20namely%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20cultural-political%20outsidership%20and%20fragmentary%20stance%20over%20history%2C%20heritages%2C%20identities%2C%20traditions%20and%20modernity.%20In%20the%20common%20philosophical%20sense%2C%20the%20quest%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20Cartesian%20%E2%80%98method%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20is%20directed%20towards%20unified%20and%20irreducible%20(as%20such%20final)%20knowledge.%20Nehru%20sought%20the%20unity%20of%20Indian%20culture%20in%20all%20its%20diversity%20and%20fragmentation.%20However%2C%20the%20heterogeneity%20and%20complexity%20of%20identity%20prompted%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20quest%20to%20be%20always%20accompanied%20by%20the%20awareness%20and%20conviction%20that%20his%20quest%20for%20historical%20and%20cultural%20sources%20and%20geneses%20of%20a%20nation%20does%20not%20meet%20with%20a%20finality%2C%20that%20Indian%20culture%20always%20hides%20something%20as%20it%20is%20discovered%20more%20and%20more.%20Such%20a%20quest%20rather%20guides%20one%20to%20identify%20a%20heterogeneous%20base%20for%20surfacing%20unity%20and%20continuity.%20Even%20the%20%E2%80%98garb%20of%20modernity%E2%80%99%20that%20is%20usually%20seen%20as%20the%20result%20of%20the%20colonial%20history%20of%20India%20(and%20with%20which%20Bhattacharjee%20begins%20his%20work)%20seems%20to%20have%20a%20much%20longer%20incubation%20in%20the%20complexity%20and%20heterogeneity%20of%20history%20and%20cultural%20identity.%20When%20the%20German%20writer%20Hubert%20Fichte%20considers%20history%20as%20strata%20(admittedly%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20etymological%20potential%20of%20German%20language%3A%20%E2%80%9CSchichten%20statt%20Geschichten%E2%80%9D)%2C%20this%20reinterpretation%20seems%20to%20correspond%20to%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20quest%20for%20a%20yet-to-be-discovered%20history%20and%20culture%20of%20India.%20An%20important%20feature%20of%20this%20seminal%20work%20by%20Bhattacharjee%20is%20the%20profound%20examination%20of%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20fateful%20encounter%20with%20history%20%E2%80%93%20in%20general%20and%20Indian%20history%20in%20particular%20%E2%80%93%20as%20discussed%20in%20the%20last%20chapters%3A%20%3Cem%3ECulture%20and%20the%20Urge%20towards%20Synthesis%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EHistory%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Roots%20of%20the%20Present%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20problem%20of%20identity%20seems%20to%20unfold%20most%20significantly%20in%20this%20encounter%20which%2C%20therefore%2C%20demands%20an%20in-depth%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBabu%20Thaliath%20is%20Professor%20and%20Chairperson%2C%20Centre%20of%20German%20Studies%2C%20School%20of%20Language%2C%20Literature%20%26amp%3B%20Culture%20Studies%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693009829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F12175342%2Fnehru-tryst-with-destiny.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fnehru-as-political-thinker%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20'Nehru%20and%20the%20Spirit%20of%20India'%2C%20Manash%20Firaq%20Bhattacharjee%20outlines%20