%20is%20right%20for%20your%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Compatibility%5C%22%3EWired%20vs.%20wireless%20gaming%20headsets%3A%20Compatibility%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22722%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20wearing%20the%20SteelSeries%20Arctis%20Nova%20Pro%20Wireless%20gaming%20headset.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e8a95c52bc2d00199205cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22541%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETop%20wireless%20gaming%20headsets%20support%20Bluetooth%20and%202.4GHz%20connections%20to%20pair%20with%20lots%20of%20devices.%3Cp%3ESteelSeries%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20wired%20gaming%20headsets%20will%20work%20across%20all%20platforms%20without%20any%20major%20compatibility%20issues.%20But%20wireless%20gaming%20headsets%20are%20another%20story.%20Wireless%20compatibility%20varies%20for%20different%20gaming%20consoles%20because%20certain%20systems%20support%20different%20types%20of%20wireless%20connections.%20The%20two%20main%20connection%20types%20are%20Bluetooth%20and%202.4GHz.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20gaming%20headsets%2C%202.4GHz%20has%20become%20popular%20since%20it%20can%20cut%20down%20on%20audio%20latency%2C%20which%20causes%20delayed%20sound%20compared%20to%20what%20you%20see%20on%20screen.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Bluetooth%20is%20more%20common%20for%20headphones%20geared%20toward%20music%20listening%20on%20your%20phone.%20However%2C%20many%20top%20wireless%20gaming%20headsets%20include%20support%20for%20both%20Bluetooth%20and%202.4GHz%20so%20you%20can%20connect%20to%20multiple%20devices%20at%20the%20same%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComputers%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fnintendo-switch-review%5C%22%3ENintendo%20Switch%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20compatible%20with%20both%20types%20of%20wireless%20signal%2C%20but%20Xbox%20and%20PlayStation%20consoles%20have%20some%20restrictions.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhere-to-buy-ps5%5C%22%3EPlayStation%205%3C%2Fa%3E%20supports%20a%20standard%202.4GHz%20wireless%20connection%2C%20but%20it%20does%20not%20support%20Bluetooth%20audio%20(though%20the%20PS4%20does).%20Xbox%20consoles%20also%20lack%20Bluetooth%20audio%20support%2C%20but%20instead%20of%20standard%202.4GHz%20capabilities%2C%20they%20use%20a%20proprietary%202.4GHz%20signal%20that%20requires%20a%20different%20type%20of%20transmitter%20than%20the%20ones%20used%20for%20PlayStation%20or%20Switch%20consoles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20pay%20close%20attention%20to%20the%20type%20of%20connection%20a%20wireless%20headset%20supports%20to%20ensure%20it%20will%20work%20on%20your%20console%20of%20choice.%20Only%20more%20expensive%20headsets%2C%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-61662-20%26h%3De80d7f920d91f383002a50f19bc395337d69433702007004d282c9567dfb1578%26postID%3D64e8a26923f4ecc1488f645c%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Ftech%252Fwired-vs-wireless-gaming-headsets%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSteelSeries-Arctis-Multi-Platform-Gaming-Mobile-Headset%252Fdp%252FB0B8QP5BGD%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteelSeries%20Arctis%20Nova%207X%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fsteelseries-arctis-nova-pro-wireless-gaming-headset-review%5C%22%3EArctis%20Nova%20Pro%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20support%20multiple%20types%20of%20wireless%20signals%20across%20PC%2C%20PlayStation%2C%20Xbox%2C%20and%20Switch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20a%20wired%20headset%20with%20a%20simple%203.5mm%20headphone%20cable%20can%20connect%20to%20all%20three%20consoles%20or%20a%20PC%20without%20any%20compatibility%20issues.%20Xbox%20and%20PlayStation%20both%20offer%20a%203.5mm%20port%20in%20their%20wireless%20controllers%2C%20so%20you%20can%20even%20use%20a%20wired%20headset%20without%20a%20cable%20connecting%20you%20to%20the%20console.%20The%20Switch%20has%20a%20built-in%203.5mm%20port%2C%20and%20it%20works%20in%20handheld%20mode%20or%20when%20the%20console%20is%20docked%20and%20connected%20to%20a%20TV.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20wired%20headset%20models%20don't%20have%20a%203.5mm%20connection%20and%20instead%20rely%20on%20a%20USB-C%20port.%20Headsets%20with%20USB-C%20are%20best%20for%20use%20with%20computers%20since%20most%20consoles%20will%20require%20you%20to%20get%20a%20USB-C%20to%203.5mm%20adapter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Sound%20quality%5C%22%3EWired%20vs.%20wireless%20gaming%20headsets%3A%20Sound%20quality%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20gamer%20playing%20while%20using%20the%20SteelSeries%20Arctis%20Pro%20wired%20headset.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fd11ffa240ebd00126bdfc1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221124%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThough%20the%20sound%20quality%20benefits%20can%20be%20subtle%2C%20a%20wired%20connection%20can%20still%20deliver%20higher%20bandwidth%20than%20a%20wireless%20signal.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETechnically%2C%20a%20wired%20audio%20connection%20can%20still%20offer%20better%20sound%20quality%20than%20a%20wireless%20connection%20since%20its%20signal%20can%20support%20a%20higher%20bandwidth%20with%20less%20interference.%20This%20means%20that%20wired%20connections%20can%20transmit%20high-quality%20lossless%20audio%20without%20any%20extra%20compression.%20That%20said%2C%20wireless%20technologies%20have%20improved%20so%20much%20that%20most%20people%20aren't%20likely%20to%20notice%20a%20difference%2C%20and%20many%20audio%20sources%20don't%20actually%20need%20the%20extra%20bandwidth%20that%20a%20wired%20connection%20provides.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20most%20important%20factors%20that%20impact%20sound%20quality%20on%20a%20gaming%20headset%20are%20the%20drivers%20(speakers)%20the%20headset%20uses%20and%20the%20source%20format%20you're%20actually%20listening%20to.%20You%20can%20find%20both%20wired%20and%20wireless%20headset%20models%20with%20high-quality%20drivers%2C%20but%20you%20can%20typically%20get%20a%20wired%20model%20with%20higher%20quality%20sound%20for%20less%20money%20than%20wireless%20options%20with%20similar%20performance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20premium%20wireless%20headsets%20do%20tend%20to%20offer%20extra%20features%2C%20like%20noise-cancellation%20and%20microphone%20monitoring%2C%20more%20often%20than%20their%20wired%20counterparts%20do.%20These%20perks%20can%20help%20improve%20your%20overall%20audio%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Latency%5C%22%3EWired%20vs.%20wireless%20gaming%20headsets%3A%20Latency%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221082%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Wyze%20Gaming%20Headset%20Dongle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e8a84052bc2d001992050d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22811%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%202.4GHz%20wireless%20connection%20can%20deliver%20lower%20latency%20than%20a%20Bluetooth%20signal.%3Cp%3EWyze%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAudio%20delay%20caused%20by%20wireless%20signals%20has%20been%20a%20polarizing%20topic%20for%20gamers%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20modern%20wireless%20headsets%20don't%20lag%20behind%20wired%20connections%20in%20meaningful%20ways.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompetitive%20gamers%20who%20want%20the%20most%20responsive%20sound%20possible%20may%20still%20opt%20for%20wired%20headphones%20to%20try%20and%20gain%20an%20advantage%2C%20but%20most%20gamers%20will%20be%20perfectly%20suited%20with%20a%202.4GHz%20wireless%20headset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBluetooth%20suffers%20from%20a%20bit%20more%20latency%20whe