ting%20automation%20company%20Klaviyo%20are%20now%20the%20first%20venture-backed%20tech%20companies%20to%20file%20for%20IPOs%20since%20December%202021.%20That's%20when%20software%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhashicorp-open-source-ipo-mitchell-hashimoto-billionaire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHashiCorp%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsamsara-ipo-founders-sanjit-biswas-john-bicket-mit-tech-billionaires-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecloud%20tech%20company%20Samsara%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20one%20thing%20Arm%2C%20Instacart%2C%20and%20Klaviyo%20have%20in%20common%3A%20profitability.%20And%20that%20may%20be%20the%20secret%20sauce%20to%20a%20successful%20public%20debut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%20revealed%20profits%20of%20%24428%20million%20in%202022%20and%20%24242%20million%20for%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%202023.%20Arm%20posted%20profits%20of%20%24524%20million%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%20that%20ended%20in%20March%20and%20%24105%20million%20for%20the%20quarter%20that%20ended%20in%20June.%20And%20Klaviyo%20reported%20a%20%2415%20million%20profit%20for%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20Instacart%20and%20Klaviyo%20are%20profitable%20could%20make%20them%20attractive%20to%20investors%20who%20became%20skittish%20in%20the%20downturn.%20The%20strong%20business%20fundamentals%20wring%20out%20some%20of%20the%20risk%20of%20such%20investments%2C%20said%20Tom%20Loverro%2C%20a%20general%20partner%20at%20IVP.%20Though%2C%20he%20says%20profitability%20isn't%20necessarily%20a%20requirement%20of%20going%20public.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20profitability%20is%20like%20the%20rule.%20But%20it's%20hard%20to%20be%20interesting.%20You%20either%20need%20to%20be%20such%20a%20rocket%20ship%20that%20people%20are%20like%2C%20'You're%20unprofitable%2C%20but%20oh%20my%20god%2C%20this%20could%20change%20the%20world.%20Take%20my%20money.'%20Or%2C%20you're%20in%20the%20bucket%20of%2C%20'I%20don't%20know%20if%20it's%20going%20to%20change%20the%20world%20but%20at%20least%20it's%20profitable.%20I'm%20less%20likely%20to%20lose%2C'%26quot%3B%20Loverro%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIPOs%20have%20been%20few%20and%20far%20between%20in%20the%20past%20year%20due%20to%20market%20volatility.%20Only%20149%20IPOs%20launched%20in%20the%20US%20last%20year%2C%20the%20lowest%20total%20since%202016.%20That's%20compared%20to%20908%20companies%20that%20went%20public%20in%202021%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fmarketintelligence%2Fen%2Fnews-insights%2Flatest-news-headlines%2Fglobal-ipo-activity-cut-nearly-in-half-in-2022-just-20-launched-in-us-during-q4-73793488%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThere%2520were%2520149%2520IPOs%2520launched%2Cfirst%2520half%2520of%2520the%2520year.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20shaky%20market%20has%20also%20caused%20venture%20capital%20investors%20to%20pull%20back%20on%20funding%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20many%20startups%20to%20raise%20funding%20and%20grow%20their%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%2C%20which%20was%20founded%20in%202012%20and%20has%20grown%20to%20be%20a%20frontrunner%20in%20the%20grocery%20delivery%20space%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-is-reportedly-planning-an-ipo-for-real-this-time-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong%20teased%20plans%20to%20go%20public%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20move%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-startups-end-ipo-hiatus-instacart-mobileye-intel-tripactions-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighly%20anticipated%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20industry%20insiders%20as%20a%20sign%20the%20IPO%20market%20is%20on%20the%20mend.%20The%20grocery%20delivery%20company's%20biggest%20backers%20include%