ts%2C%20and%20are%20found%20nowhere%20else%20in%20the%20world.%20Such%20as%20the%20White-bellied%20blue%20flycatcher%2C%20a%20small%20songbird%20that%20you%20can%20spot%20only%20in%20the%20Western%20Ghats%20of%20south%20India.%20Some%20are%20habitat%20specialists%3A%20they%20are%20found%20only%20in%20some%20habitats%20in%20the%20country.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGreat%20Indian%20bustards%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20are%20ground-dwellers%20and%20are%20restricted%20to%20open%20habitats%20such%20as%20grasslands%20that%20are%20broadly%20known%20as%20open%20natural%20ecosystems%20or%20ONEs.%20Generalists%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20are%20species%20that%20can%20thrive%20and%20adapt%20to%20more%20habitat%20types%20and%20food%20resources.%20Such%20as%20the%20national%20bird%2C%20the%20Indian%20peafowl.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215433%2FIndian-Peafowl-Albin-Jacob.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215433%2FIndian-Peafowl-Albin-Jacob.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215433%2FIndian-Peafowl-Albin-Jacob-300x180.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215433%2FIndian-Peafowl-Albin-Jacob-1024x613.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669903%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22718%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIndian%20Peafowl.%20Photo%3A%20Albin%20Jacob%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20understand%20how%20birds%20are%20faring%20in%20the%20country%2C%2013%20institutions%20in%20India%20(six%20government%20institutions%20including%20the%20Wildlife%20Institute%20of%20India%20and%20seven%20conservation%20NGOs)%20and%20independent%20professionals%20came%20together%20to%20analyse%20data%20on%20bird%20distribution%20and%20population%20trends%20of%20942%20bird%20species%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20this%2C%20they%20relied%20mostly%20on%20bird%20observation%20data%20collected%20by%20citizen%20scientists%20%E2%80%93%20a%20whopping%2030%20million%20bird%20observations%20or%20bird%20lists%20uploaded%20by%2030%2C000%20bird%20watchers%20and%20nature%20enthusiasts%20%E2%80%93%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Febird.org%2Findia%2Fhome%5C%22%3EeBird%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20online%20database%20of%20bird%20observations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20researchers%20analysed%20the%20long-term%20trends%20in%20bird%20populations%20(changes%20over%2030%20years)%20and%20the%20current%20annual%20trends%20(annual%20changes%20over%20the%20past%20eight%20years).%20They%20also%20analysed%20birds%E2%80%99%20distribution%20range%20sizes%20across%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20they%20found%20is%20worrying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDecline%2C%20overall%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%20338%20species%20that%20had%20enough%20data%20to%20assess%20for%20long-term%20trends%2C%2060%25%20of%20the%20species%20showed%20long-term%20declines.%20The%20trends%20showed%20that%20204%20species%20have%20declined%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%2098%20species%20declined%20rapidly%2C%2098%20species%20are%20more%20or%20less%20stable%2C%20and%2036%20species%20showed%20increases.%20Of%20the%20359%20species%20analysed%20for%20current%20annual%20trends%2C%2040%25%20are%20declining.%20The%20current%20trends%20showed%20that%20142%20species%20are%20declining%20(of%20which%2064%20are%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Crapid%20decline%E2%80%9D)%2C%20189%20are%20stable%20and%2028%20are%20increasing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215930%2FAsian-Koel-Female-Abhishek-Das.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215930%2FAsian-Koel-Female-Abhishek-Das.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215930%2FAsian-Koel-Female-Abhishek-Das-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215930%2FAsian-Koel-Female-Abhishek-Das-683x1024.jpg%20683w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669905%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAsian%20Koel%20Female.%20Photo%3A%20Abhishek%20Das%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20results%2C%20presented%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstateofindiasbirds.in%2F%23soib_methods%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EState%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Birds%20report%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20show%20that%20while%20a%20few%20generalists%20like%20the%20Indian%20peafowl%20and%20Asian%20koel%20are%20thriving%20in%20India%2C%20many%20others%2C%20especially%20habitat%20specialists%20such%20as%20birds%20found%20in%20grasslands%20and%20wetlands%2C%20are%20in%20rapid%20decline.%20Birds%20that%20feed%20on%20vertebrates%20and%20carrion%20%E2%80%93%20including%20raptors%20(specifically%20habitat-specialist%20raptors%20such%20as%20some%20harriers%20and%20the%20Short-toed%20snake%20eagle)%2C%20and%20vultures%20%E2%80%93%20have%20declined%20greatly.%20This%20could%20be%20suggestive%20of%20harmful%20pollutants%20in%20their%20food%20resources%2C%20a%20decline%20in%20prey%20availability%2C%20or%20both%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInsectivorous%20birds%20are%20also%20in%20peril.%20The%20SoIB%202023%20notes%20that%20b%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eirds%20endemic%20to%20the%20Western%20Ghats%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%20biodiversity%20hotspot%20have%20rapidly%20declined%20in%20India%20over%20the%20past%20few%20decades.%20The%20reasons%20behind%20this%20decline%2C%20however%2C%20are%20not%20clear%2C%20the%20report%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20groups%20of%20birds%20that%20are%20facing%20declines%20include%20grassland%20birds%20such%20as%20the%20Great%20grey%20shrike%20(which%20has%20faced%20a%20decline%20of%20more%20than%2080%25)%20and%20Great%20Indian%20bustards.%20Wetland%20species%20and%20shorebirds%20such%20as%20the%20dainty%20curlew%20sandpiper%20have%20also%20witnessed%20declines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CConsidered%20globally%20Near%20Threatened%2C%20this%20species%20%5Bcurlew%20sandpiper%5D%20used%20to%20be%20observed%20in%20large%20numbers%20in%20key%20Indian%20wintering%20sites%20like%20Point%20Calimere%20and%20Pulicat%20Lake%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20it%20has%20undergone%20a%20decline%20over%20the%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20existence%20of%20Pulicat%20Lake%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20the%20second%20largest%20brackish%20water%20lake%20in%20India%2C%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Factivists-request-tn-cm-stalin-to-scrap-kattupalli-port-expansion%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecurrently%20under%20threat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Local%20communities%20and%20activists%20are%20protesting%20against%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20Adani%20run-Kattupalli%20Port.%20The%20expansion%20will%20impact%20the%20Lake%20in%20several%20ways%20that%20will%20affect%20both%20the%20wildlife%20and%20people%20who%20depend%20on%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESome%20increases%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20few%20generalist%20bird%20species%20are%20doing%20extremely%20well%20in%20the%20country%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20This%20includes%20the%20national%20bird%2C%20the%20Indian%20peafowl.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20150%25%20increase%20in%20the%20abundance%20of%20peafowl%20across%20the%20country%20over%20the%20past%20decades%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20Peafowl%2C%20which%20occurred%20only%20in%20two%20districts%20in%20Kerala%20in%201998%20and%20was%20extremely%20rare%20in%20the%20state%2C%20now%20occurs%20in%20all%20districts.%20However%2C%20this%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fpeafowls-kerala-climate-change%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20necessarily%20a%20good%20thing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20good%20news%20of%20the%20increase%20in%20peafowl%20must%20be%20tempered%20by%20a%20recognition%20of%20increased%20reports%20of%20crop%20damage%20(and%20consequent%20retaliatory%20poisoning)%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20and%20the%20speculation%20that%20rising%20peafowl%20populations%20may%20have%20negative%20impacts%20on%20snakes%20and%20other%20reptiles%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20conservation%20tends%20to%20focus%20on%20rare%20and%20declining%20species%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20investigate%20the%20impacts%20of%20this%20peafowl%20boom%20on%20both%20people%20and%20ecosystems.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20species%20that%20are%20doing%20remarkably%20well%20are%20the%20Ashy%20Prinia%2C%20the%20feral%20Rock%20pigeon%2C%20and%20the%20Asian%20koel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215639%2FAshy-Prinia-Bhaarat-Vyas.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215639%2FAshy-Prinia-Bhaarat-Vyas.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215639%2FAshy-Prinia-Bhaarat-Vyas-300x182.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669904%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22389%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAshy%20Prinia.%20Photo%3A%20Bhaarat%20Vyas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESpecies%20of%20high%20conservation%20priority%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBased%20on%20these%20data%20and%20the%20species%E2%80%99%20listing%20in%20the%20International%20Union%20for%20Conservation%20of%20Nature%20(IUCN)%2C%20the%20SoIB%202023%20report%20classified%20all%20942%20species%20into%20three%20categories%20for%20priority%20action.%20It%20has%20classified%20178%20species%20as%20High%20Priority%2C%20323%20as%20Moderate%20Priority%2C%20and%20441%20as%20Low%20Priority.%20The%20High%20Priority%20species%20include%20migratory%20wetland%20birds%20like%20the%20Ruddy%20shelduck%2C%20resident%20species%20such%20as%20the%20Indian%20courser%2C%20endemics%20such%20as%20the%20Narcondam%20hornbill%20which%20is%20found%20only%20on%20the%20small%2C%20roughly%207%20sq%20km%20Narcondam%20island%20in%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20islands%20and%20the%20Nicobar%20megapode%20on%20Nicobar%20island.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%20High%20Priority%20species%2C%2090%20are%20classified%20as%20globally%20of%20Least%20Concern%20by%20the%20IUCN%20Red%20List%202022.%20The%20report%20recommended%20that%2017%20of%20these%20would%20qualify%20for%20a%20different%20IUCN%20threat%20status%20nationally.%20These%20include%20the%20Indian%20Roller%2C%20a%20grassland%20and%20scrub%20bird%20which%20shows%20a%2030%25%20decline%20in%2012%20years%2C%20and%20the%20Northern%20shoveler%2C%20a%20species%20of%20duck%20that%20shows%20a%2058%25%20decline%20in%2014%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstateofindiasbirds.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2FSOIB_Web-version_Final_.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20SoIB%20report%20in%202020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20also%20showed%20similar%20trends%20of%20decline%20in%20bird%20populations%20in%20India.%20The%202020%20report%20relied%20on%20more%20than%2010%20million%20observation%20records%2C%20contributed%20by%20over%2015%2C500%20birdwatchers%20in%20India.%20The%20latest%20SoIB%20report%2C%20however%2C%20is%20a%20wider%20assessment%3A%20it%20uses%20more%20data%2C%20and%20details%20the%20status%20of%20942%20species%20(as%20opposed%20to%20867%20in%20the%20previous%20one).%20Out%20of%20the%20101%20birds%20categorized%20as%20High%20Concern%20(i.e.%2C%20Priority)%20in%202020%2C%2074%20remain%20in%20the%20same%20category%2C%20the%20new%20report%20noted.%20An%20additional%20104%20species%20have%20been%20newly%20listed%20as%20High%20Priority%20in%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENeed%20more%20action%2C%20research%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20highlighted%20several%20major%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbird-population-decline%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethreats%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20including%20forest%20degradation%2C%20urbanization%20and%20energy%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%93%20that%20bird%20species%20face%20across%20the%20country.%20Environmental%20pollutants%20including%20veterinary%20drugs%20such%20as%20nimesulide%20still%20threaten%20vulture%20populations%20in%20India%2C%20it%20noted.%20Of%20concern%20also%20are%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20(such%20as%20on%20migratory%20species)%2C%20avian%20disease%20and%20illegal%20hunting%20and%20trade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20points%20to%20the%20need%20to%20conserve%20specific%20groups%20of%20birds.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20grassland%20specialists%20have%20declined%20by%20more%20than%2050%25%20%E2%80%93%20indicating%20the%20importance%20of%20protecting%20and%20maintaining%20grassland%20ecosystems.%20Per%20the%20report%2C%20systematic%20monitoring%20of%20bird%20populations%20over%20long%20periods%20of%20time%20is%20critical%20to%20understanding%20small-scale%20changes%20in%20bird%20populations.%20It%20is%20becoming%20clearer%20that%20we%20also%20need%20more%20research%20to%20understand%20the%20reasons%20behind%20the%20declines%20or%20increases%2C%20scientists%20on%20the%20team%20said%2C%20in%20an%20online%20press%20conference%20on%20August%2025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20laws%20and%20policies%20are%20largely%20framed%20around%20what%20we%20need%20to%20do%20to%20save%20threatened%20species%20but%20equally%20we%20need%20to%20keep%20common%20species%20common%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Suhel%20Quader%2C%20senior%20scientist%20at%20the%20Nature%20Conservation%20Foundation%2C%20one%20of%20the%20partner%20organisations%20that%20collaborated%20on%20the%20report.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20abundant%2C%20widespread%20species%20that%20are%20providing%20several%20ecosystem%20services%2C%20he%20added.%20Policies%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20river%2C%20water%2C%20or%20wasteland%20development%20policies%20%E2%80%93%20must%20also%20converge%2C%20he%20said.%20Currently%2C%20they%20sometimes%20act%20in%20opposition%20to%20each%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20example%2C%20wasteland%20development%20may%20act%20in%20opposition%20to%20conservation%20needs%20of%20ONEs%20and%20their%20biodiversity%20so%20we%20need%20to%20see%20how%20we%20can%20rationalize%20these%20policies%20so%20that%20conservation%20can%20be%20a%20part%20of%20all%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Quader%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%2C%20an%20outcome%20of%20observation%20records%20contributed%20by%20a%20large%20number%20of%20birdwatchers%20across%20India%2C%20augurs%20well%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Findias-citizen-scientists-rake-in-bird-sightings-second-only-to-us-in-global-bird-count%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecitizen%20participation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20is%20an%20important%20contributor%20towards%20biodiversity%20conservation%2C%20said%20Ravi%20Singh%2C%20Secretary%20General%20and%20CEO%20of%20WWF-India%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20partner%20organizations%20of%20the%20effort.%20%E2%80%9CFollowing%20this%20report%2C%20the%20next%20step%20should%20be%20an%20action%20plan%20for%20conservation%20of%20bird%20populations%20and%20habitats.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692981426000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25215050%2FThe-Wire.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fstate-of-indias-birds-new-report-reveals-a-story-of-few-gains-but-many-losses%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20is%20based%20on%2030%20million%20observations%20by%2030%2C000%20birdwatchers.%20While%20generalist%20species%20like%20the%20Indian%20peafowl%20are%20doing%20well%2C%20many%20others%2C%20including%20habitat%20specialists%20and%20raptors%20aren't.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fstate-of-indias-birds-new-report-reveals-a-story-of-few-gains-but-many-losses%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Autoworkers%20Authorize%20Strikes%20Against%20Ford%2C%20General%20Motors%20And%20Stellantis%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22The%20contracts%20for%20150%2C000%20autoworkers%20expire%20next%20month%2C%20creating%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20large-scale%20walkout.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692981258000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fimg.huffingtonpost.com%2Fasset%2F64e8cb5a23000062003f70a1.jpeg%3Fcache%3DPSnJ9GUUs0%26ops%3D1200_630%22%2